Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.09,0:04:06.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I was getting crowded here, and they left. It seems comical, huh? All right, so today I thought
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.87,0:04:13.83,Default,,0,0,0,,a number of you are familiar with the work I've done, and so I'm going to recapitulate it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.62,0:04:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I will tell you how it all originated, you know. I had a huge psychiatric practice, and
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.80,0:04:28.70,Default,,0,0,0,,it was the largest in the United States, frankly, and we had a couple of thousand outpatients,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.46,0:04:34.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and I had a huge staff, and we treated the most hopeless patients from all over the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.62,0:04:41.64,Default,,0,0,0,,They flew them in from every country, and some had very rich parents. They were Maharaj in India,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.64,0:04:47.05,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, multi, huge amount of money, and so these patients had been everywhere,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.23,0:04:52.46,Default,,0,0,0,,seeing everybody. They'd seen every professor, and they're all hopeless, the most hopeless of
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.46,0:05:00.27,Default,,0,0,0,,all cases. So those were the patients that I specialized, the most hopeless of all, and we used
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.77,0:05:10.01,Default,,0,0,0,,alternate therapies. Medical science itself calibrates as a science about 440, but clinical
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.01,0:05:15.81,Default,,0,0,0,,science, that's academic science, calibrates around 440. Clinical science calibrates five
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.81,0:05:24.61,Default,,0,0,0,,points higher, 445. So it takes into account the effect of the healer, the presence of the
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.61,0:05:32.03,Default,,0,0,0,,physician, and the consciousness level of the physician, too, you see. So I had a huge staff,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.05,0:05:39.17,Default,,0,0,0,,of psychiatrists, and I noticed that some had very high rates of recovery, and others didn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.29,0:05:44.47,Default,,0,0,0,,As it turned out later, those with the higher levels of consciousness had the highest rating
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.47,0:05:57.35,Default,,0,0,0,,of healings, because they brought the power of intention, and the power of intention. We'll get
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.35,0:06:03.31,Default,,0,0,0,,around to quantum mechanics later, but the Heisenberg principle, you understand, precipitates
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.92,0:06:14.83,Default,,0,0,0,,potentiality becoming an actuality. And what hasn't been measured is the power of the effect of
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.83,0:06:23.11,Default,,0,0,0,,the observer. It's taken as an abstract concept in the work of Henry Stapp at Berkeley, explains the
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.11,0:06:30.36,Default,,0,0,0,,scientific basis of it. But what we haven't measured yet is there's a difference between the
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.36,0:06:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness level of the observer. So a person with a weak level of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.94,0:06:44.02,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't experience miracles, doesn't even see miracles. And to other people, the miraculous is a
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.02,0:06:50.50,Default,,0,0,0,,continuous reality. The fact that I'm alive and breathing today is already a miracle.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.77,0:07:09.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I didn't want to listen to him talk all morning. So I was gonna tell you how this all started.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.15,0:07:12.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So, yes. So, we had a Course in Miracles group, so we knew that there was a certain thing that was going to be
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.26,0:07:13.22,Default,,0,0,0,,in my life at the end of the day. And I don't know about you, but I knew that I would have to go to my
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.22,0:07:13.66,Default,,0,0,0,,best friends and friends, and I knew that I was going to have to go to my best friends, and my best friend was going to have to go to my best friend. And I knew that he had
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.66,0:07:20.87,Default,,0,0,0,,group there. It was the second, whatchamacallit, healing center in the United States. The first
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.87,0:07:28.60,Default,,0,0,0,,one was in Tiburon, and Jerry came out with his whole staff and spoke to our staff. So
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.60,0:07:33.49,Default,,0,0,0,,we had the second attitudinal healing center in the United States based on the Course in
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.49,0:07:38.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Miracles. That was for hopeless patients at the clinic. And so we had patients with every
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.35,0:07:44.23,Default,,0,0,0,,kind of disease known to mankind who practiced the Course in Miracles. So I had studied something
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.23,0:07:48.07,Default,,0,0,0,,about kinesiology. I'd heard that that's a new way you could diagnose and help treat
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.07,0:07:54.27,Default,,0,0,0,,patients. And so I went and learned about it, and I came back to lecture to the staff
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.27,0:07:58.91,Default,,0,0,0,,about what I had learned. And I found that there were certain people, oh, I know what
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.91,0:08:05.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I did. I said, I need some volunteers for the kinesiology demonstration tonight. And
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.26,0:08:12.70,Default,,0,0,0,,a few of them were hanging out because they were meeting with the attitudinal healing
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.70,0:08:17.52,Default,,0,0,0,,center. And I said, come on over here, let me see, and we'll test you tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.56,0:08:25.58,Default,,0,0,0,,So when I tested them with fluorescent lights or pesticides, things that make everybody
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.58,0:08:34.01,Default,,0,0,0,,go weak, these people did not go weak. In teaching kinesiology, I used to just, you
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.01,0:08:42.91,Default,,0,0,0,,pass out synthetic sugar substitutes or pesticides or look at fluorescent lights, everybody goes
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.91,0:08:47.74,Default,,0,0,0,,weak looking at fluorescent lights. But these people did not. They looked at the fluorescent
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.74,0:08:49.42,Default,,0,0,0,,light and their arms stayed strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.44,0:08:54.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, what's the matter with this guy? Then I tried pesticides. That didn't make
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.88,0:08:59.88,Default,,0,0,0,,them go weak either. So something was different about this group that was doing the Course
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.88,0:09:09.13,Default,,0,0,0,,in Miracles from ordinary people. So a new group was starting doing the Course in Miracles.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.13,0:09:16.71,Default,,0,0,0,,So I tested them periodically. I tested them about once a week. And of course, they went
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.71,0:09:20.15,Default,,0,0,0,,weak to fluorescent lights. These fluorescent lights would make everybody go weak.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.31,0:09:25.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And then I found around less than 90 or so, after they'd been in the Course about three
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.55,0:09:31.59,Default,,0,0,0,,months, suddenly negative stimuli did not make them go weak anymore. I said, wow-zee,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.59,0:09:33.58,Default,,0,0,0,,that's fantastic.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.58,0:09:41.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And from that, we then devised a measuring system of one to a thousand. And kinesiology
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.52,0:09:49.19,Default,,0,0,0,,is not understood by people at all. They think it has to do with, they don't understand that
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.19,0:09:50.19,Default,,0,0,0,,it's objective.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.04,0:09:59.66,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, in the presence of truth, physiologically, you go strong via your acupuncture
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.66,0:10:07.55,Default,,0,0,0,,system. And there's other physiologic phenomena, such as the pupillary response. So some people
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.55,0:10:12.27,Default,,0,0,0,,like to ridicule kinesiology. It's because they don't understand it. Because people who
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.27,0:10:17.75,Default,,0,0,0,,are stuck in the linear pedestrian domain of intellectual development don't understand
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.75,0:10:18.75,Default,,0,0,0,,the non-linear.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.75,0:10:20.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, the skeptics...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.07,0:10:27.99,Default,,0,0,0,,are stuck with the fact that they have a very pedestrian mentality. Below 200, you
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.99,0:10:36.13,Default,,0,0,0,,don't understand the non-linear domain. Because reality emerges as a consequence, not only
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.13,0:10:43.29,Default,,0,0,0,,of content, but of context. And the skeptic is unaware of the power of the field, the
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.29,0:10:50.48,Default,,0,0,0,,non-linear field of context. Consequently, a physician who believes in God has a higher
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.48,0:10:51.48,Default,,0,0,0,,cure rate. They want to know what the cure rate is. They want to know what the cure rate
