Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.34,0:16:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It goes up very, very rapidly as you get into higher numbers.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.76,0:16:51.76,Default,,0,0,0,,As you get into higher numbers.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.76,0:16:57.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore a loving thought is, I forget how many times, 10 million or some odd number,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.96,0:16:59.94,Default,,0,0,0,,more powerful than a negative thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.94,0:17:05.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So stop feeling guilty about your negative thoughts, because they're weak and feeble.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.72,0:17:09.62,Default,,0,0,0,,One loving thought will undo all the negative thoughts you've had all day.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.62,0:17:13.94,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a fact, oh Lord, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.94,0:17:14.94,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.94,0:17:15.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I never asked that one.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.94,0:17:16.44,Default,,0,0,0,,But.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.70,0:17:19.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I just know it experientially.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.26,0:17:22.76,Default,,0,0,0,,One loving thought is transformative.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.76,0:17:24.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It undoes all the negatives.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.36,0:17:25.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.36,0:17:33.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you see, here you're hitting somebody, the power of that is 20, 20 times 10, 10 times
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.65,0:17:39.37,Default,,0,0,0,,10, 20 times, 10 times 10, 20 times.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.37,0:17:43.57,Default,,0,0,0,,A loving thought is 10 times 10, 500 times.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.57,0:17:45.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You see how enormously powerful.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.92,0:17:46.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.92,0:17:49.58,Default,,0,0,0,,A loving thought is.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.58,0:17:52.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So to be, people say, how do you reach enlightenment?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.78,0:17:58.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I say, be loving towards all of life and all of its expressions at all times.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.45,0:18:00.27,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.27,0:18:02.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Goodwill and lovingness towards all of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.55,0:18:06.83,Default,,0,0,0,,So that lovingness, it isn't love, it's lovingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.83,0:18:09.59,Default,,0,0,0,,See, love here is at 500.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.59,0:18:14.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Lovingness is maybe at about 540 on up to 570.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.74,0:18:16.58,Default,,0,0,0,,540 is the 12 step groups.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.58,0:18:17.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Alcoholics Anonymous.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.62,0:18:24.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Unselfish lovingness and goodwill towards others.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.35,0:18:32.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So as you advance spiritually, that which you hold in mind tends to manifest.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.69,0:18:39.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And you also discover if you have any negative thoughts, too, as you hear something falling
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.73,0:18:44.49,Default,,0,0,0,,off the wall, you say, well, God, I didn't really mean to think that.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.49,0:18:47.24,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.24,0:18:48.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.24,0:18:56.20,Default,,0,0,0,,What happens then is what people are critical about kinesiology and they can't get off their
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.20,0:18:58.98,Default,,0,0,0,,own narcissistic orientation towards life.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.98,0:19:05.58,Default,,0,0,0,,They presume that everything we say or every calibration is a personal opinion.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.58,0:19:08.90,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't get appearance from essence.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.90,0:19:13.20,Default,,0,0,0,,There's appearance and then there's essence, as Descartes pointed out.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.20,0:19:17.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And the difficulty, as Socrates says, is man cannot differentiate appearance from essence.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.60,0:19:18.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The essence is the innate essence.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.60,0:19:19.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The essence is the innate essence.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.60,0:19:20.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The essence is the innate truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.88,0:19:23.42,Default,,0,0,0,,That which is how it is in nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.42,0:19:24.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Appearance is what you think about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.70,0:19:28.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not interested in what anybody thinks about anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.90,0:19:33.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not interested in anybody's opinion about anything because opinions are worthless.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.63,0:19:39.91,Default,,0,0,0,,You can go on the Internet and there's millions and millions of and you calibrate them, they're
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.91,0:19:40.91,Default,,0,0,0,,all under 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.91,0:19:45.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, 200 is a magic number.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.32,0:19:49.66,Default,,0,0,0,,We found that anything below 200 makes you go weak and anything over 200 makes you go
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.66,0:19:51.01,Default,,0,0,0,,strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.49,0:19:59.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And for the first time, the first time in all of human history, there was a way of discerning
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.02,0:20:00.02,Default,,0,0,0,,truth from falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.02,0:20:06.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know that in one second, we can discern the truth or the falsehood of anything, anywhere
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.78,0:20:13.69,Default,,0,0,0,,in time, anywhere in the universe?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.69,0:20:19.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Fifteen percent of the audience got what I said, 85 percent do not.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.20,0:20:22.36,Default,,0,0,0,,By the end of the day, we hope we'll increase this.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.36,0:20:23.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Why is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.36,0:20:25.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Because in the infinite dimensionless field of the universe, there's nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.24,0:20:26.24,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.24,0:20:27.26,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.26,0:20:28.26,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no center.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.26,0:20:29.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing is present, there is not.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.55,0:20:30.55,Default,,0,0,0,,There is nothing in the infinite realm.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.55,0:20:31.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is a field of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.55,0:20:32.55,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no center.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.55,0:20:35.81,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no center to an infinite universe, neither is there a past or a present or a
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.81,0:20:36.81,Default,,0,0,0,,future.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.81,0:20:43.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, everything is happening now, yours is discernable now, and everywhere is right
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.73,0:20:45.62,Default,,0,0,0,,here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.62,0:20:55.46,Default,,0,0,0,,What Napoleon thought about and how he felt before he walked into the Pyramid and how
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.46,0:21:00.07,Default,,0,0,0,,he felt after he walked out of the Pyramid is knowable right this instant.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.07,0:21:02.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.03,0:21:05.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Because outside of time, there is no then, now, or future.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.95,0:21:09.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You cannot use kinesiology to determine the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.41,0:21:11.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Why is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.49,0:21:13.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the future is not a reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.35,0:21:16.37,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a hypothetical potentiality.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.43,0:21:20.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So the future isn't set.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.65,0:21:25.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, books telling you about the prophecies of the future all calibrate negative.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.03,0:21:26.77,Default,,0,0,0,,All of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.95,0:21:28.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Not a single one of them calibrates true.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.82,0:21:30.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.18,0:21:38.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Because potentiality is actualizing based on an infinite field.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.36,0:21:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And part of the infinite field is your decision from moment to moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.56,0:21:47.29,Default,,0,0,0,,The future hasn't happened yet because we haven't created it yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.41,0:21:49.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Because what we're holding in mind is what's creating the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.45,0:21:52.81,Default,,0,0,0,,How can you predict that which has no reality?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.02,0:21:54.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It has no reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.86,0:21:56.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So you cannot predict the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.26,0:22:01.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to understand me.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.47,0:22:03.35,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.35,0:22:03.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.37,0:22:05.01,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.13,0:22:06.49,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't predict the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.21,0:22:12.33,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why in the New Testament, the book of Revelations, calibrates it 70.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.99,0:22:26.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I treated a lot of people with apocalyptic triumphalism delusions.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.93,0:22:31.03,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a realm in the lower astral, calibrates it 70.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.77,0:22:33.49,Default,,0,0,0,,People periodically go over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.49,0:22:37.91,Default,,0,0,0,,There was somebody here in Sedona, very well known, who had quite a few fathers.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.27,0:22:43.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And he had gone over there and was predicting end times, etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.91,0:22:53.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Because at that calibrated level of 70, there's an astral realm where the apocalyptic catastrophic is a continuous ongoing play.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.89,0:23:01.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you go out of body, your spirit goes over there, you experience it as a reality, you come back here and tell everybody that the end is coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.11,0:23:06.41,Default,,0,0,0,,And every generation, there's people walking up and down the sidewalks, repent, the end is coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.37,0:23:15.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The future isn't here because we haven't created it yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.36,0:23:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,In human experience, the collective consciousness of mankind, which was at 190,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.64,0:23:28.16,Default,,0,0,0,,the collective consciousness of mankind calibrated at 90 at the time of the birth of the Buddha.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.82,0:23:32.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It calibrated about 100 at the time of the birth of Jesus Christ.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.20,0:23:37.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It slowly rose over the centuries and got as far as about 190.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.20,0:23:40.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And there it stayed for many centuries.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.26,0:23:41.62,Default,,0,0,0,,It stayed right at 190.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.66,0:23:46.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And up until the late 1980s.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.44,0:23:52.74,Default,,0,0,0,,It was at 190 and then suddenly in the late 1980s, it jumped to 205.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.34,0:24:02.74,Default,,0,0,0,,It then, a couple of years later, that we were lecturing in San Francisco when it did it, it went from 205 to 207 at the time of the Harmonic Concordance.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.96,0:24:06.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And since that time, it has gone back down again.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.57,0:24:07.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see what it is this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.67,0:24:10.97,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to take the world's temperature every day, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.39,0:24:12.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.17,0:24:16.15,Default,,0,0,0,,The collective consciousness of mankind, we have permission to ask that or resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.79,0:24:18.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It's currently over 204.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.32,0:24:20.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Currently over 205.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.38,0:24:21.82,Default,,0,0,0,,204.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.10,0:24:23.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So it was up to 207.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.68,0:24:25.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It went down to 204.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.44,0:24:29.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I was a little disappointed.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.98,0:24:33.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought it was going to keep evolving in a steady course, but it didn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.54,0:24:38.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So, for reasons, I don't know myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.58,0:24:39.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't worry about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.50,0:24:39.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't worry about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.16,0:24:48.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The consciousness of...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.25,0:24:57.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know if there's any tax points on it for now, but I hope I do with the states,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.32,0:25:04.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and history has, you know, the basic idea of the us has a certain Norman.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.12,0:25:08.79,Default,,0,0,0,,So, that thing you have been questioning it lately.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.23,0:25:09.97,Default,,0,0,0,,My pleasure.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.17,0:25:12.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I was so told so many things that it was almost like a golden age.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.09,0:25:14.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the kind of lights that keepOnly a boost out of the earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.13,0:25:16.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So of course, we'd get stuck on rotation.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.57,0:25:18.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It's been about five years, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.02,0:25:18.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And historically...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.64,0:25:19.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And historically, we have looked.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.72,0:25:19.96,Default,,0,0,0,,A lot, perhaps.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.96,0:25:20.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow, wow.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.28,0:25:33.32,Default,,0,0,0,,is that? Singapore is over 430, 435. Singapore is ahead of us. I think they're so good. Well,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.32,0:25:47.77,Default,,0,0,0,,where do they see our new iPod-y-doodle? iPod-y-doodle, where do they see our new iPod-y-doodle?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.77,0:25:57.12,Default,,0,0,0,,That'll show them Singaporeans. Level of consciousness, then, is correlated with your
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.12,0:26:04.82,Default,,0,0,0,,understanding of divinity, your view of yourself. The level of consciousness here, we've depicted
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.82,0:26:11.90,Default,,0,0,0,,it all the way from enlightenment down to suicidal shame, the logarithm, the emotion that goes with
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.90,0:26:18.64,Default,,0,0,0,,it, and the process going on in consciousness itself. And as you'll notice, these are all very
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.64,0:26:27.59,Default,,0,0,0,,destructive down here. Then you become a good deal freer. You begin to transcend, transfigure,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.59,0:26:32.63,Default,,0,0,0,,illumination, and reach the states of enlightenment, which are really from 600 and up.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.63,0:26:41.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I say the 12-step groups are at about 540. Sainthood is at about 570. Mother Therese,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.20,0:26:49.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Sainthood, who's, let's see, who's the 570? Father Pio, various people,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.33,0:26:57.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Sainthood, the last Pope was 570. This Pope is 565, which is practically the same range. So,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.71,0:27:02.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I have respect for the Pope, and you don't have to be a Catholic to respect the fact that his
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.95,0:27:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,commitment is to Christianity as he understands it. Okay. And the Dalai Lama, various people,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:11.00,0:27:19.96,Default,,0,0,0,,uh-huh. And anyway, that's neither here nor there. We'll go on to the next thing. Where's the next,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.96,0:27:21.58,Default,,0,0,0,,what'd you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.58,0:27:21.82,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.82,0:27:32.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Where's the next slide? Oh. This is the world's population, the distribution of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.42,0:27:38.50,Default,,0,0,0,,throughout the world. And you see, here's the level of truth to integrity at 200. Everything
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.50,0:27:46.13,Default,,0,0,0,,below here is false. Everything below 200 is false and destructive. You see that approximately 80
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.13,0:27:52.35,Default,,0,0,0,,percent of the world's population lives in the destructive realm of consciousness. There are
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.35,0:28:02.93,Default,,0,0,0,,countries where 100 percent of the people are below 200. Therefore, our diplomatic attempts at
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.93,0:28:08.77,Default,,0,0,0,,conciliation with serenity, peace, honesty, and truth do not go too far in certain places in the
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.77,0:28:19.27,Default,,0,0,0,,world because this truth sounds to these people like falsehood. So, there's a flip side. We'll
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.27,0:28:27.10,Default,,0,0,0,,show in a kind of slide later. This flip side has to do with, actually, with brain physiology. From
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.10,0:28:32.86,Default,,0,0,0,,200, consciousness level 200, which is commitment to truth and integrity for its own sake, not for
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.86,0:28:41.58,Default,,0,0,0,,personal gain, uh, people process with a different side of the brain. So, these people here process
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.58,0:28:47.94,Default,,0,0,0,,primarily with the animal side of the brain. And once the kundalini energy begins to rise, the
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.94,0:28:53.38,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness level 200, the kundalini energy begins to rise. Once it does, it shifts your brain
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.38,0:28:57.46,Default,,0,0,0,,processing to right brain, and you see and experience things differently. So, you see and experience things
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.46,0:29:04.98,Default,,0,0,0,,differently because the brain physiology processes things differently. And we have a slide on that
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.98,0:29:13.31,Default,,0,0,0,,later. Therefore, how approximation is going to be brought between civilizations, one processes
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.31,0:29:19.15,Default,,0,0,0,,things with the animal instinct side of the brain, and this one processes things with the kundalini
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.15,0:29:25.26,Default,,0,0,0,,energy side of the brain. And how you're going to get an approximation, I have no idea. That's why
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.26,0:29:29.34,Default,,0,0,0,,we need God. God, we need God.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.34,0:29:30.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You know.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.08,0:29:39.81,Default,,0,0,0,,He said, you already got help. I said, oh, yes, you got help, cause you gotta solve this conundrum of
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.81,0:29:47.43,Default,,0,0,0,,how, what you're gonna do about all this. So, the purpose to my life of, to my way of seeing of human
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.43,0:29:59.32,Default,,0,0,0,,life is that this world is perfect the way it is. I'm not interested in improving the world. Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.32,0:30:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the world as it is, is absolutely perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.92,0:30:06.70,Default,,0,0,0,,It's designed to be perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.70,0:30:14.46,Default,,0,0,0,,is for the advancement of human consciousness and if that is the purpose
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.46,0:30:20.41,Default,,0,0,0,,of human life, the advancement of consciousness, then this is the perfect
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.41,0:30:27.74,Default,,0,0,0,,world. What's the karmic merit if you don't have anybody to hate, you know
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.74,0:30:37.78,Default,,0,0,0,,what I'm saying? Who's there to forgive? All right, so anyway, we'll move on to the next.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.78,0:30:44.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is the distribution of consciousness levels of mankind and you
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.69,0:30:48.71,Default,,0,0,0,,see people from 200 and up, which characterizes an audience like this, and
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.71,0:30:52.67,Default,,0,0,0,,the naivety of these people is they project this onto the world and think
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.67,0:31:00.10,Default,,0,0,0,,these people are like you. They are not like you. You feel constrained to tell
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.10,0:31:05.56,Default,,0,0,0,,the truth. In their mind, to tell the truth is idiotic and stupid, can probably
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.56,0:31:10.92,Default,,0,0,0,,get you killed if not fired or executed, because your duty is to do what brings
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.92,0:31:11.32,Default,,0,0,0,,gain.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.32,0:31:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Period. Not truth. Telling the truth will get you executed in a good part of
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.00,0:31:25.77,Default,,0,0,0,,this living world today. Uh-huh. Contrary. So you've got a 180. So in understanding
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.77,0:31:29.73,Default,,0,0,0,,the world then, you have to understand that many people think completely the
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.73,0:31:39.11,Default,,0,0,0,,opposite from which you do. Uh-huh. We consider benevolence a virtue. Half the
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.11,0:31:43.26,Default,,0,0,0,,world considers benevolence a despicable weakness.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.26,0:31:50.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Weakness. Okay. So this helps us understand how to deal with the world and
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.33,0:31:54.89,Default,,0,0,0,,especially international diplomacy. All right, we'll move to the next one. Uh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.89,0:32:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,How people see. You see, as a psychiatrist and psychoanalyst, when a patient comes
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.96,0:32:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,,in, it's not his responsibility to understand where I am. It's my
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.68,0:32:09.53,Default,,0,0,0,,responsibility to understand where he is. And we're walking around the world
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.53,0:32:13.53,Default,,0,0,0,,saying, you should understand where we are. No, we should understand where they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.53,0:32:16.03,Default,,0,0,0,,so we know how to communicate with them, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.03,0:32:17.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So what we think is a lovely idea,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.65,0:32:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,they think is ridiculous, yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.00,0:32:24.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is just the way the whole thing balances out.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.86,0:32:27.74,Default,,0,0,0,,What you see is that although there's very few people
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.74,0:32:29.30,Default,,0,0,0,,at the top of the pyramid,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.30,0:32:32.04,Default,,0,0,0,,their power is so enormous that they counterbalance
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.04,0:32:34.46,Default,,0,0,0,,the negativity of the rest of the population.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.46,0:32:37.10,Default,,0,0,0,,What you need is a few people, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.10,0:32:39.18,Default,,0,0,0,,in a very high level of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.18,0:32:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,to counterbalance all the negativity of an entire country.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.48,0:32:44.08,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's move on to the next.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.48,0:32:50.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Calibration level 1,000, for instance, of the great avatar,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.41,0:32:54.09,Default,,0,0,0,,1,000 will counterbalance all the negativity
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.09,0:32:56.20,Default,,0,0,0,,of all of mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.20,0:32:59.32,Default,,0,0,0,,All you need is one enlightened teacher on the planet
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.32,0:33:02.80,Default,,0,0,0,,to counterbalance the total negativity of all of mankind
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.58,0:33:05.28,Default,,0,0,0,,because it's a logarithmic progression,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.36,0:33:07.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and 10 times 10 times 10,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.90,0:33:11.74,Default,,0,0,0,,a thousand times is a significant amount of power.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.74,0:33:13.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So we'll move to the next one.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.60,0:33:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.96,0:33:20.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's move back to the last one, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.20,0:33:25.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, this is evolution of consciousness over elapsed time.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.82,0:33:28.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And you see it was practically at a standstill
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.86,0:33:33.24,Default,,0,0,0,,for millions of years, and this is the way it's moving now.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.24,0:33:37.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is why I thought, well, consciousness is going to go up,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.02,0:33:40.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and lately it's been going down a few points,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.82,0:33:44.34,Default,,0,0,0,,which we'll have to change the graph and put a squiggle in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.34,0:33:45.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Squiggle.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.16,0:33:53.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, well, move to the next one, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.74,0:33:57.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, so this is the evolution of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.44,0:34:01.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, to understand the evolution of the ego,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.44,0:34:06.62,Default,,0,0,0,,you understand out of the radiance of divinity,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:06.62,0:34:09.04,Default,,0,0,0,,out of the light of divinity shown forth,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.80,0:34:15.14,Default,,0,0,0,,its interaction with matter and organic matter spawned life.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.22,0:34:17.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So life emerged.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.22,0:34:17.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.36,0:34:23.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Life emerged as a consequence of the presence of the infinite power of divinity
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.04,0:34:27.12,Default,,0,0,0,,in its interaction with material world.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.30,0:34:29.08,Default,,0,0,0,,That's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:29.84,0:34:33.35,Default,,0,0,0,,The light of divinity, when it's shown upon matter,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.97,0:34:37.63,Default,,0,0,0,,out of that arose organicity, and out of that arose life.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:38.27,0:34:46.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The most primitive forms of life, of course, animal life, protoplasmic life,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.30,0:34:50.22,Default,,0,0,0,,does not have within itself a source of energy,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.64,0:34:51.65,Default,,0,0,0,,not a source of energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.65,0:34:53.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Not a single rabbit, not a single protozoa.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.59,0:34:56.21,Default,,0,0,0,,They all have to get energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.41,0:34:59.47,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, vegetative life has chlorophyll,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.75,0:35:01.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and if you're a plant, all you've got to do is sit there.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.70,0:35:05.66,Default,,0,0,0,,The sun shines on you, and you get all the energy you need.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.72,0:35:07.54,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to acquire or get.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.09,0:35:13.77,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're protoplasmic, however, you won't live very long unless you get energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.89,0:35:15.05,Default,,0,0,0,,You have no source of energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.13,0:35:15.93,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.51,0:35:19.05,Default,,0,0,0,,To get energy, you have to sample what's out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.05,0:35:22.15,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're a little amoeba, you have to try this, you have to try that.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.15,0:35:25.21,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, a little sip of this, and then .
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.15,0:35:34.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Over the millennia, life then learned that which is favorable to life and that which is unfavorable.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.14,0:35:37.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you didn't learn that, you didn't exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.76,0:35:39.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't survive.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.40,0:35:51.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, the ego is constantly that quality of life which samples everything experientially
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.26,0:35:54.36,Default,,0,0,0,,to discern is it pro-life or anti-life.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.36,0:36:05.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the kinesiologic response then, if it's over 200, the life energy gets that this is pro-life,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.26,0:36:06.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and she goes strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.13,0:36:15.93,Default,,0,0,0,,If it's anti-life, below 200, the little proto, the little amoeba in her senses that and goes weak.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.93,0:36:17.79,Default,,0,0,0,,It says, no, don't eat that.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:18.79,0:36:23.61,Default,,0,0,0,,That's automatized over the millennia in the autonomic nervous system
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.61,0:36:25.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and in the acupuncture system.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:25.67,0:36:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So, if I hold something in mind, I don't even have to tell her what it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:34.27,0:36:36.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I'm going to hold something in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:37.20,0:36:46.47,Default,,0,0,0,,What I'm holding in mind calibrates over 400, 450, 480, 475.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.47,0:36:48.33,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a painting by Degas.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.54,0:36:51.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And she doesn't know what I was holding in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:51.36,0:36:52.08,Default,,0,0,0,,You can see that.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.04,0:36:59.97,Default,,0,0,0,,A painting by Degas of the ballet dancers, you know, a very entrancing impressionistic painting.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.09,0:37:02.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Calibrates at 480.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.44,0:37:17.37,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you see how life then evolved over time, calibrated level of life overall.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.37,0:37:22.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The first signs of life were then bacteria and algae calibrated at one.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.67,0:37:29.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And marine invertebrates, cephalopods, and then we go up to the mammalian life.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:29.03,0:37:33.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Calibrated level of evolution, calibrated level of life over the eons.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:33.69,0:37:37.25,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll go to the next next slide.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.50,0:37:43.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So, here you see bacteria.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:43.48,0:37:47.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we said, what is the lowest level that we can say life emerges as bacteria?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.24,0:37:51.10,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll call that one.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.10,0:37:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And what's the highest it reaches?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:52.80,0:37:58.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And we found that at 1,000, the great avatars, Jesus Christ, Buddha, Krishna,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.10,0:38:01.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Zoroaster, all calibrated at 1,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.79,0:38:08.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Highest energy of life experientially in this world, therefore, are the great avatars at 1,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:08.69,0:38:10.09,Default,,0,0,0,,They represent, therefore,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.09,0:38:12.86,Default,,0,0,0,,In this range is the absolute.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.86,0:38:17.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, there's nothing relativist hate worse than the thought of an absolute.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:17.94,0:38:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Because their idea of reality is reality is whatever you think it is, and project out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.08,0:38:26.60,Default,,0,0,0,,They think that perception is reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.60,0:38:28.02,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:28.02,0:38:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,These numbers are all essence.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.48,0:38:32.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Perception is not reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.08,0:38:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Essence is reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.76,0:38:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,If anything is only what you think it is, then there is no reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.88,0:38:41.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And if there's no reality, then there's no reality to their statement, that,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.80,0:38:44.56,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:44.56,0:38:50.62,Default,,0,0,0,,The way to get rid of deconstructionism is you can deconstruct deconstructionism, because
Dialogue: 0,0:38:50.62,0:38:54.02,Default,,0,0,0,,the premise is that all premises are false, that means the premise is that all things
Dialogue: 0,0:38:54.02,0:38:57.62,Default,,0,0,0,,are false is false, so that's the end of relativism.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.62,0:39:05.97,Default,,0,0,0,,No, the absolute, some people have reviewed some of my work somewhere, and he warns the
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.97,0:39:13.53,Default,,0,0,0,,reader, beware, he's an absolutist.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:13.53,0:39:19.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Autism means responsibility, doesn't it, means yes, you are accountable, yeah, means
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.66,0:39:22.49,Default,,0,0,0,,your karma is what counts, all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.49,0:39:30.43,Default,,0,0,0,,So here we go, you see protozoa, crustaceans, insects, amphibians, did anybody see the Blue
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.43,0:39:31.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Planet the other night?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:31.43,0:39:37.43,Default,,0,0,0,,The Blue Planet reruns on TV, if you haven't seen the Blue Planet, be sure to see it, it's
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.43,0:39:42.03,Default,,0,0,0,,so stunningly beautiful, and people who don't believe in intelligent design, I tell them,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.03,0:39:43.03,Default,,0,0,0,,watch the Blue Planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.03,0:39:43.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And then call me later.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.89,0:39:48.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And tell me if you still don't believe in intelligent design, the exquisite beauty and
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.43,0:39:53.77,Default,,0,0,0,,the absolute perfection of the evolution of all things at the bottom of the sea, mysterious
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.77,0:39:54.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and entrancing.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.77,0:40:00.51,Default,,0,0,0,,You watch these little things down there, they're incredible beauty, and their ingenuity,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.51,0:40:04.69,Default,,0,0,0,,this little diddly light gets you to bite and come over and try and eat me, and then,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.69,0:40:09.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I got you, smarts.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.82,0:40:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Unintelligent life is nowhere to be found.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.92,0:40:17.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It killed itself off millennia ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.68,0:40:18.68,Default,,0,0,0,,There's only intelligent.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.68,0:40:26.10,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, arachnids, the fish, you see, the octopus, I love the octopus, they're the smartest
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.10,0:40:34.65,Default,,0,0,0,,thing around, 20, and you see the Komodo dragon, don't go in the cage with them, and if you
Dialogue: 0,0:40:34.65,0:40:43.80,Default,,0,0,0,,do, always wear your shoes, some idiot went in the cage with a Komodo dragon without his
Dialogue: 0,0:40:43.80,0:40:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,shoes on.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.80,0:40:49.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, he lived to tell the tale, God bless him.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:49.32,0:40:56.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Snakes and alligators, and all kinds of wiggly, screamy things, dinosaurs, whales, dolphins,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.32,0:41:01.68,Default,,0,0,0,,whales, and all these kind of things, aha.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:01.68,0:41:05.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So down here you see dinosaurs.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:05.34,0:41:12.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know that there are a large percentage of people on the planet that are at this level,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.18,0:41:16.38,Default,,0,0,0,,that of the reptile, reptile, there are actually people out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.38,0:41:25.56,Default,,0,0,0,,These serial killers that kill lots of children, they calibrate at 35, less than a reptile, aha.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.56,0:41:30.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you notice that life in here has to destroy other life in order to survive.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.54,0:41:34.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The polar bears got to pounce on a seal and eat it.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.38,0:41:40.30,Default,,0,0,0,,All these animals here, wolves and all these, live by killing others.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:40.30,0:41:46.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And then at level about 200, you see the emergence of the herbivores.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:46.56,0:41:53.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And who do not have to kill anything in order to live, they live on vegetation.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.24,0:42:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And so here you see a shift from carnivorous predators to benign, the grazers, deer and
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.48,0:42:08.28,Default,,0,0,0,,domestic pigs and elk, dairy cows, the sheep, range cattle, and now we're getting over 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.28,0:42:10.51,Default,,0,0,0,,That's very interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.51,0:42:13.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we're very, very interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.21,0:42:15.33,Default,,0,0,0,,You can relate to these animals.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.33,0:42:16.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And elephants at 235.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.43,0:42:17.43,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:17.55,0:42:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,A kitty is at 240, and a family kitty that's loved is 245.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:23.92,0:42:27.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Dogs at 245.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.21,0:42:30.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Then we go up through the monkeys, the gorillas.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:30.25,0:42:34.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Alex, the trained African great parrot, is at 400.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.87,0:42:38.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Coco, the trained gorilla, is at 405.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:38.08,0:42:43.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you realize you are safer in a cage with Coco than 90% of the people on this planet?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:43.98,0:42:49.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Coco's not out to do you any harm.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.82,0:42:55.94,Default,,0,0,0,,He's not trying to sell you anything, isn't going to kill you in the name of peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:55.94,0:43:01.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Coco says, either be peaceful or I'll kill you.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.70,0:43:09.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the most amazing thing, and we still don't have the answer, is a cat's purr calibrates
Dialogue: 0,0:43:09.82,0:43:15.11,Default,,0,0,0,,at 500, which is the level of love, as does a dog's wagging tail.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:15.11,0:43:18.07,Default,,0,0,0,,They have literally the capacity to love.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:18.07,0:43:19.13,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why when I hear a cat's purr, I'm like, wow.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.13,0:43:19.89,Default,,0,0,0,,That's great.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.89,0:43:23.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I had a practice, and I would have a depressed patient living alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:23.45,0:43:27.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd say, I'm not going to treat you unless you get her a cat or a dog.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:27.55,0:43:32.17,Default,,0,0,0,,You need something to think about except your own self all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.17,0:43:37.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And the cat's purr at 500 and the dog's wagging tail at 500.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:37.33,0:43:38.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:38.33,0:43:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, kinesiology is very useful.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:41.28,0:43:46.23,Default,,0,0,0,,We use it all the time because you can know the unknowable.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.23,0:43:49.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You can know the unknowable.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.26,0:43:50.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Right now, we've got a sick kitty at home.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:50.26,0:43:51.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And so I can find out his medication.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.26,0:43:52.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's check out kitty at home.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:52.29,0:43:53.29,Default,,0,0,0,,We can check out kitty at home right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:53.29,0:43:54.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Right now, he's feeling comfortable.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.29,0:43:55.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:55.29,0:43:56.29,Default,,0,0,0,,He's got pain, but the medication is handling it.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:56.29,0:43:57.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So we should keep the dose of the medication the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:57.42,0:43:58.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Give it to him every other day.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:58.42,0:43:59.42,Default,,0,0,0,,He needs antibiotics right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:59.42,0:44:00.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.42,0:44:01.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:01.42,0:44:02.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Do we have them on him?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:02.42,0:44:03.74,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:03.74,0:44:05.09,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:05.09,0:44:06.09,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:06.09,0:44:07.09,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:07.09,0:44:08.09,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:08.09,0:44:09.09,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:09.09,0:44:10.09,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:10.09,0:44:11.09,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:11.09,0:44:12.09,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.09,0:44:13.09,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:13.09,0:44:14.16,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:14.16,0:44:15.16,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:15.16,0:44:16.16,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:16.16,0:44:17.16,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.16,0:44:18.16,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:18.16,0:44:19.57,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:19.57,0:44:20.57,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:20.57,0:44:21.57,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:21.57,0:44:22.76,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:22.76,0:44:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:23.76,0:44:24.76,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:24.76,0:44:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:27.84,0:44:28.84,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:28.84,0:44:29.84,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:29.84,0:44:30.84,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:30.84,0:44:33.99,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:33.99,0:44:34.99,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:34.99,0:44:35.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:35.99,0:44:36.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Now that saved a big bill at the veterinarian, didn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:36.99,0:44:37.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I think he might be anemic.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:37.99,0:44:38.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Phil, let me check here.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:38.99,0:44:40.99,Default,,0,0,0,,He has clinical anemia, is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:40.99,0:44:42.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I knew he would get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:42.99,0:44:43.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:43.99,0:44:44.99,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, he's got a bleeding lesion, he's got anemia.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:44.99,0:44:48.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So he's a little cat, but we've got the diagnosis on him.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:48.35,0:44:49.73,Default,,0,0,0,,We know everything we need to know about him.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:49.73,0:44:54.09,Default,,0,0,0,,We know whether he operates, if we raise him on medication, his pain.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:54.09,0:44:54.99,Default,,0,0,0,,So I can know the unknowable.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:54.99,0:44:55.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:55.99,0:45:04.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So, many things in your life will become unknowable and now you have a way to instantly know the
Dialogue: 0,0:45:04.48,0:45:05.48,Default,,0,0,0,,truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:05.48,0:45:07.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to have permission to ask the question.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:07.32,0:45:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I don't always verbalize it in front of an audience because it's on repetition,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:12.00,0:45:17.48,Default,,0,0,0,,but I ask before I ask it, I have permission to ask this question.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:17.48,0:45:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:18.48,0:45:22.26,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I don't need it.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:22.26,0:45:24.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I have permission to ask this question.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:24.20,0:45:29.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And occasionally, we will get a no, and in fact, we've gotten no in front of large audiences
Dialogue: 0,0:45:29.14,0:45:34.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and we didn't know the reason for the no and we didn't have time to research it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:34.30,0:45:37.56,Default,,0,0,0,,There's probably some things that are better not to know.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:37.56,0:45:42.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Got in his wisdom, keeps us ignorant of certain things, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:42.68,0:45:46.54,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll move on to the next.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:46.54,0:45:53.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Now the thing that's, okay, this is the relationship between the linear and the nonlinear.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:53.87,0:45:54.87,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:54.87,0:45:55.71,Default,,0,0,0,,The linear.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:55.71,0:45:58.79,Default,,0,0,0,,The linear is like science.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:58.79,0:46:03.93,Default,,0,0,0,,It's discernible and it operates according to, or it seems to operate according to Newtonian
Dialogue: 0,0:46:03.93,0:46:06.01,Default,,0,0,0,,principles of cause and effect.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:06.01,0:46:11.18,Default,,0,0,0,,It's definable, identifiable, it's a world of science.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:11.18,0:46:14.95,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the world, the Newtonian world of causality.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:14.95,0:46:22.05,Default,,0,0,0,,However, what the Newtonian world of causality ignored until just recently in quantum mechanics
Dialogue: 0,0:46:22.05,0:46:24.25,Default,,0,0,0,,is that it doesn't exist in a vacuum.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:24.25,0:46:25.39,Default,,0,0,0,,It exists in a field.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:25.39,0:46:28.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Infinite field.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:28.40,0:46:30.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Infinite field of infinite power.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:30.46,0:46:36.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So the only reason the linear works is because of the power of the infinite field of the
Dialogue: 0,0:46:36.86,0:46:39.23,Default,,0,0,0,,nonlinear.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:39.23,0:46:45.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So you take a potentiality all by itself, something that's linear, nothing will happen
Dialogue: 0,0:46:45.14,0:46:50.46,Default,,0,0,0,,unless you, you know, you might say electrify it, put it in an infinite field of power,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:50.46,0:46:56.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and now that which is intention becomes an actuality.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:56.08,0:46:57.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So things come about then.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:57.64,0:47:06.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It's sort of a karmic emergence, karmic too, karmic and karmic, the emergence of potentiality
Dialogue: 0,0:47:06.06,0:47:08.52,Default,,0,0,0,,depending on local conditions.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:08.52,0:47:13.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore your own intention has a very powerful effect.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:13.15,0:47:19.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The less selfish the intention, the greater the likelihood that it will manifest.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:19.56,0:47:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,If you, to want, crave, desire, and gotta have, tends to block it, tends to block it.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:27.36,0:47:28.36,Default,,0,0,0,,To hold it in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:28.36,0:47:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Every place I've lived all the last, well, a lot of years now, well over 50 years, every
Dialogue: 0,0:47:34.40,0:47:40.38,Default,,0,0,0,,place that I've lived, I had only envisioned, I just pictured what I thought, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:40.38,0:47:48.27,Default,,0,0,0,,would really love to have, and it would always just magically appear, where I live now, was
Dialogue: 0,0:47:48.27,0:47:49.72,Default,,0,0,0,,the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:49.72,0:47:54.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I just held in mind that which would be ideal, and the next thing you know, somebody would
Dialogue: 0,0:47:54.96,0:47:58.52,Default,,0,0,0,,call me and say, you know what, there's a property next door to me and it's for sale,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:58.68,0:48:01.44,Default,,0,0,0,,that's how the place I live now came about.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:01.44,0:48:06.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And back east, I just envisioned a place in the woods and a place in the woods came about.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:06.54,0:48:13.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So what you hold in mind then tends to manifest because there's an infinite field, which
Dialogue: 0,0:48:13.84,0:48:18.40,Default,,0,0,0,,is consciousness, divinity, you might say, the omnipotence of divinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:18.40,0:48:23.58,Default,,0,0,0,,The proximate field is what you're holding in mind, proximate field.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:23.58,0:48:27.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And then the content is, let's say, you want a house or a car, a pretty maiden, whatever,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:27.90,0:48:28.90,Default,,0,0,0,,whatever.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:28.90,0:48:33.42,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll move on to the next.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:33.42,0:48:39.62,Default,,0,0,0,,The content then, we say, is the ego, it's linear, it's measurable.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:39.62,0:48:45.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The spiritual ego, here's the nonlinear dynamics and the quantum mechanics, the context is
Dialogue: 0,0:48:45.38,0:48:52.39,Default,,0,0,0,,the spirit, which is nonlinear, unlimited, self-existent, we call it spiritual.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:52.39,0:48:57.77,Default,,0,0,0,,It's demonstrable, we demonstrate it using kinesiology.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:57.77,0:49:00.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, what's the next one now?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:00.88,0:49:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I forget what number we're on.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:02.88,0:49:05.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Eighteen.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:05.51,0:49:06.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Eighteen, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:06.51,0:49:07.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:07.80,0:49:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Where's my magnifying glass?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:08.80,0:49:09.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't have a magnifying glass.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:09.80,0:49:15.34,Default,,0,0,0,,How am I going to see what's there?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:15.34,0:49:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, anyway, things get dimmer as you get older, I don't know, it's just that the universe
Dialogue: 0,0:49:23.44,0:49:24.44,Default,,0,0,0,,does that.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:24.44,0:49:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The universe gets dimmer.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:25.44,0:49:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It has nothing to do with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:30.48,0:49:31.48,Default,,0,0,0,,What number are we at?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:31.48,0:49:33.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Eighteen.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:33.15,0:49:34.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, eighteen.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:34.15,0:49:37.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so, alright.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:37.33,0:49:41.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, somebody's got to keep track of the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:41.59,0:49:43.59,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll have to take a break at what time?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:43.59,0:49:44.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Five more minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:44.59,0:49:45.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, my god.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:45.59,0:49:46.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I better hurry up.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:46.59,0:49:47.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:47.59,0:49:53.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Quantum mechanics, because it's important to understand quantum mechanics.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:53.51,0:49:57.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't become enlightened without quantum mechanics.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:57.76,0:50:08.15,Default,,0,0,0,,The Schrodinger equations denote the current state of the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:08.15,0:50:11.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Through the Heisenberg principle, you make a choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:11.15,0:50:16.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And then you collapse the wave function, and you do it via the von Neumann process, and
Dialogue: 0,0:50:16.91,0:50:21.15,Default,,0,0,0,,then by calculating the Dirac, you can calculate.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:21.15,0:50:29.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the potentiality then becomes an actuality via the Heisenberg process.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:29.42,0:50:33.22,Default,,0,0,0,,That was the discovery, that you cannot do the same experiment twice, because merely
Dialogue: 0,0:50:33.22,0:50:40.01,Default,,0,0,0,,witnessing and observing an experiment already changes the outcome, the introduction of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:40.01,0:50:49.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So, Stapp is the most advanced physicist in my idea of understanding.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:49.90,0:50:57.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So, as we teach, everything is in a state of potentiality awaiting to be collapsed into
Dialogue: 0,0:50:57.02,0:51:03.12,Default,,0,0,0,,an actuality, collapse the wave function from potentiality into actuality.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:03.12,0:51:06.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, what you hold in mind tends to manifest.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:06.12,0:51:12.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you picture yourself in whatever condition you think would be ideal, and let go of one
Dialogue: 0,0:51:12.12,0:51:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,of the two.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:13.12,0:51:19.49,Default,,0,0,0,,You want it, desire it, or crave it, and you surrender it to God.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:19.49,0:51:23.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead of trying to make it happen, you allow it to happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:23.49,0:51:28.91,Default,,0,0,0,,So, spiritual work is not yang, it's yin.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:28.91,0:51:35.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I would say every position that I've advanced through this lifetime has been a yin.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:35.26,0:51:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,To thee, O Lord, do I surrender my will in the matter, instead of yang.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:42.48,0:51:45.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the ego is very yang and very linear.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:45.48,0:51:48.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And it is out there on the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:48.84,0:51:52.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The yin, now.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:52.06,0:51:58.16,Default,,0,0,0,,The thing is, as you know from the 91st Psalm, in the statement of Krishna, those who call
Dialogue: 0,0:51:58.16,0:52:02.16,Default,,0,0,0,,upon me are mine, and God cannot refuse you.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:02.16,0:52:10.58,Default,,0,0,0,,God is unable to refuse your legitimate appeal or resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:10.58,0:52:11.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:11.58,0:52:15.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You ever hear that one before?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:15.48,0:52:16.51,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:19.11,0:52:22.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So, that which supplicates infinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:22.11,0:52:31.39,Default,,0,0,0,,If infinity then is almost, well, it's the wrong word, but obligated, you might say,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:31.39,0:52:32.39,Default,,0,0,0,,to respond.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:32.39,0:52:38.35,Default,,0,0,0,,However, you may get a no, because of your own karmic propensity.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:38.35,0:52:46.79,Default,,0,0,0,,So, on the way down from 13,000 feet, you can undo a lot of negative karma.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:47.79,0:52:53.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And at the end, you probably, that got rid of the last of that negative karma.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:53.98,0:53:00.75,Default,,0,0,0,,All the people you killed all over your lifetimes, you look at the history of mankind and think
Dialogue: 0,0:53:00.75,0:53:03.75,Default,,0,0,0,,how many people you probably killed in previous lifetimes.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:03.75,0:53:08.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Killing others was the way life was, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:08.61,0:53:13.61,Default,,0,0,0,,When the Vikings came over, they didn't capture slaves, they slaughtered them all.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:13.61,0:53:14.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:14.61,0:53:19.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The Visigoths, the history of mankind is you slaughter your enemies.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:19.61,0:53:24.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Consequently, the karmic inheritance of mankind, then, has to do with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:24.93,0:53:28.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Again, has to do with the undoing of a good deal of manslaughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:28.93,0:53:31.93,Default,,0,0,0,,If you have permission to ask this, resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:31.93,0:53:33.93,Default,,0,0,0,,That is true, oh Lord, resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:33.93,0:53:36.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, the undoing of a good deal of negative karma.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:36.93,0:53:41.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Say to yourself as you break your leg or whatever, well, that gets rid of that negative karma.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:48.18,0:53:50.18,Default,,0,0,0,,That gets rid of that negative karma.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:50.18,0:53:53.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything serves the purpose of evolution.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:53.18,0:53:55.18,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a perfect world.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:55.18,0:54:00.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Because to gain karmic merit, you have to have the option of making a mistake and refuse the mistake
Dialogue: 0,0:54:00.18,0:54:02.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and this time choose correctly.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:02.18,0:54:04.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Otherwise, there's no karmic merit, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:04.18,0:54:06.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:06.18,0:54:10.18,Default,,0,0,0,,So, in your karmic bank account is going up and going down.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:10.18,0:54:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And, of course, so this world is a world that is perfect for the evolution of human consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:54:17.44,0:54:24.44,Default,,0,0,0,,to go from the lower levels, the linear, the animal instincts, to shift from this side of the brain,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:25.44,0:54:30.12,Default,,0,0,0,,you pray to the Lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:30.12,0:54:33.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You're asking for the kundalini energy to rise.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:33.12,0:54:40.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The kundalini energy then rises and as it does, it shifts your whole perception of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:40.12,0:54:42.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The world looks differently.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:42.28,0:54:45.24,Default,,0,0,0,,You all look friendly.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:45.24,0:54:48.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody here is friendly.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:48.14,0:54:54.45,Default,,0,0,0,,If there isn't anybody who's not here and is not friendly, I'll beat them up until they're friendly.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:54.45,0:54:57.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Beat them until they are friendly.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:57.45,0:55:00.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Who is that king that would beat his subjects until they loved him?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:01.61,0:55:05.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll beat him until he loves me.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:05.61,0:55:13.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we attract to ourselves that which we are.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:13.84,0:55:16.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, when we leave the body, where do we go?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:16.84,0:55:19.84,Default,,0,0,0,,We go to that which we already are.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:19.84,0:55:22.93,Default,,0,0,0,,That's it. I have permission to ask that.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:22.93,0:55:24.93,Default,,0,0,0,,That is a fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:24.93,0:55:29.93,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to worry about it after death because you're only going to go to that which you already are.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:29.93,0:55:32.67,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't go to something different.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:32.67,0:55:37.67,Default,,0,0,0,,We're all like little magnetic filings in a great electrostatic field.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:37.67,0:55:40.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you automatically go to that which you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:40.89,0:55:47.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So, by free choice, by option, you say yes to this option, like a little piece of iron filing.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:47.89,0:55:50.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Your positive end and you got a negative end.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:50.89,0:55:55.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So, as you choose love like this and you choose hate there, you choose love.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:55.89,0:56:02.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So, like a little iron filing, you can see your spirit is constantly moving, shifting in an infinite field of infinite power.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:02.89,0:56:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Which we call God.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:06.40,0:56:11.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, the justice of God is absolute.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:11.40,0:56:13.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Not arbitrary.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:13.50,0:56:22.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Not a cranky old man who gets mad at you.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:22.64,0:56:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The justice of God is automatic.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:26.00,0:56:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,In an infinite electromagnetic field, there is no injustice.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:30.00,0:56:35.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Every single little filing is exactly where it is based on its polarity.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:35.03,0:56:38.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And as you say yes, oh, heck with it, I'll forgive him.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:38.03,0:56:39.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You move to this side.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:39.03,0:56:43.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You say, son of a bitch, I want to kill that bastard.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:43.03,0:56:45.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You move to this side.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:45.03,0:56:50.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And you can see where you are is the consequence of that which you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:50.35,0:56:56.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Consequently, there's no point to fear an arbitrary God who's like a nasty old crank.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:56.35,0:57:01.37,Default,,0,0,0,,The God of the Old Testament is, you know, an anthropomorphic weirdo, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:01.37,0:57:06.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So, gets all jealous, upset, has his favorites, plays favorite.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:06.50,0:57:08.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't need a God for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:08.50,0:57:09.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Your next door neighbor is a...
Dialogue: 0,0:57:09.50,0:57:17.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, Freud ridiculed that.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:17.65,0:57:21.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And, of course, I agree with Freud about that myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:21.65,0:57:28.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The anthropomorphic understandings of God are in predictions of the child-parent relationship from the unconscious.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:28.78,0:57:33.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Freud then made the mistake, if there's no false God, therefore there's no true God.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:33.78,0:57:38.20,Default,,0,0,0,,So, Freud calibrated 499, genius.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:38.20,0:57:40.20,Default,,0,0,0,,But he didn't get to 500.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:41.20,0:57:47.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And the fact that the false depictions of God are false doesn't mean that the true ones are not true.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:47.20,0:57:51.20,Default,,0,0,0,,So, he jumped beyond the level of logic.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:51.20,0:57:54.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And, of course, I myself was psychoanalyzed.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:54.20,0:57:56.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And my analyst...
Dialogue: 0,0:57:56.20,0:57:58.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Freud was really my great-grandfather.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:58.20,0:58:03.20,Default,,0,0,0,,My analyst was Lionel Oversee, whose analyst was analyzed by Freud.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:03.20,0:58:06.20,Default,,0,0,0,,So, Freud's my great-grandfather.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:08.20,0:58:10.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I had a Freudian analysis.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:10.20,0:58:12.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I was very young then.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:12.20,0:58:20.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And then I saw Harry Thiebaud, who was the foremost psychoanalyst in analyzing the ego and the unconscious.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:20.20,0:58:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And you just brought in dreams.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:23.20,0:58:26.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, I had about three different kinds of psychoanalysis.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:26.20,0:58:32.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And then spent the next 50 years listening to some 25,000 people.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:32.20,0:58:39.29,Default,,0,0,0,,25,000 people from a psychiatric, psychoanalytic, psychological viewpoint and treating that many.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:39.29,0:58:47.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And the way I'm describing things is a composite of that totality of experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:47.92,0:58:48.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Psychoanalytic.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:48.92,0:58:54.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I also had experiences, which I've written about in books, which were unusual, starting at age three.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:54.92,0:58:57.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Have I got enough time for that?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:57.11,0:59:00.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes or no?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:00.71,0:59:03.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll just do a brief one, and then we'll have a quick break.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:03.96,0:59:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,But this lifetime was unusual.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:06.96,0:59:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Statistically, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:08.96,0:59:13.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, there was absolute oblivion until age three.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:14.35,0:59:24.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Age three, out of oblivion, out of the oblivion of nothingness, suddenly there occurred, with a terrible shock, the awareness of existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:24.35,0:59:27.35,Default,,0,0,0,,From nothingness to existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:27.35,0:59:29.35,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a terrible shock.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:29.35,0:59:31.35,Default,,0,0,0,,A severe shock.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:31.35,0:59:33.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I still haven't gotten over it.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:33.35,0:59:40.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Every once in a while, I rediscover that I exist, and it comes back as a shock again.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:40.08,0:59:45.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Because in many lifetimes, I was a Hinayana Buddhist.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:45.11,0:59:51.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I negated the linear, and I would go into the void, and I would leave that lifetime in the void.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:51.11,0:59:55.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So anyway, at age three, suddenly I came into the awareness of existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:55.11,1:00:01.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Existence versus nonexistence was the puzzle and the conundrum of this entire lifetime.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:01.11,1:00:04.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I was not pleased to discover I exist.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:04.84,1:00:06.84,Default,,0,0,0,,A three-year-old body.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:06.84,1:00:09.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Not only did you exist, but a body went with it.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:09.84,1:00:13.77,Default,,0,0,0,,A three-year-old body sitting in a wagon.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:13.77,1:00:16.73,Default,,0,0,0,,This is all nonverbal.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:16.73,1:00:19.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Just a stunning awareness of existence as existence.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:19.73,1:00:25.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Then came, as soon as you realize you exist, up comes the fear of nonexistence.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:25.86,1:00:26.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Instantly.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:26.86,1:00:31.86,Default,,0,0,0,,If you identify with existence as a reality, you instantly are stuck with the fear of nonexistence.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:31.86,1:00:38.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So at age three, there I was, stuck with the conundrum of, is the infinite reality existence or nonexistence?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:38.86,1:00:44.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't solve that one until consciousness level 850.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:44.30,1:00:48.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It took some 30 years to solve that one.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:48.30,1:00:50.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:50.36,1:00:53.16,Default,,0,0,0,,What was I telling you this for?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:53.16,1:00:55.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I forget.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:55.26,1:00:57.90,Default,,0,0,0,,What was I going to tell him?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:03.16,1:01:04.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:04.16,1:01:07.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I was brought up very, very religious.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:07.16,1:01:08.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Episcopal, high Episcopal.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:08.16,1:01:12.26,Default,,0,0,0,,My great-grandfather was an Episcopal bishop.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:12.26,1:01:14.26,Default,,0,0,0,,We were very religious.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:14.26,1:01:16.45,Default,,0,0,0,,And I was very religious.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:16.45,1:01:18.45,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, I suffered from scrupulosity.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:18.45,1:01:21.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I worried about having a sin all the time.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:21.45,1:01:22.45,Default,,0,0,0,,. . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . .
Dialogue: 0,1:01:22.45,1:01:26.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought the soul was like a big blank screen, and if you sinned, it blotched up there,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:26.45,1:01:29.45,Default,,0,0,0,,somebody threw an egg on it, and God would see this sin on your soul.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:29.45,1:01:33.45,Default,,0,0,0,,So I was scared to death of having a sin that God was going to see, you know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:33.45,1:01:39.48,Default,,0,0,0,,God's looking at your soul, and here you got all these black spots on your soul.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:39.48,1:01:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So if I had any kind of a negative thought, I really had a fit about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:42.48,1:01:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I had to go for counseling about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:44.48,1:01:46.67,Default,,0,0,0,,. . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . .
Dialogue: 0,1:01:46.67,1:01:49.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I lived in fear of sin.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:49.99,1:01:51.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I was an acolyte in church, you know, and I was an acolyte for the church.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:51.99,1:01:58.79,Default,,0,0,0,,church, you know, and I was an acolyte for the bishop. And I was a boy soprano, an excellent
Dialogue: 0,1:01:58.79,1:02:03.83,Default,,0,0,0,,boy soprano, stunningly good boy soprano. Well, you can say that when you're objective
Dialogue: 0,1:02:03.83,1:02:14.68,Default,,0,0,0,,about yourself. And I sang in the Greek choir, and I was the boy soloist. And when I sang
Dialogue: 0,1:02:14.68,1:02:21.22,Default,,0,0,0,,the soprano obbligato above a full choir, paunus angelicus, with a full choir, a full
Dialogue: 0,1:02:21.22,1:02:29.67,Default,,0,0,0,,orchestra, and a full organ, it was entrancing. It was entrancing to the witness because while
Dialogue: 0,1:02:29.67,1:02:36.99,Default,,0,0,0,,people presume I'm a me, I'm not a me, I'm the witness. And so, I remember witnessing
Dialogue: 0,1:02:36.99,1:02:44.93,Default,,0,0,0,,the voice coming out. It was as though an angelic being sang through the voice. The
Dialogue: 0,1:02:44.93,1:02:51.71,Default,,0,0,0,,audience went into tears, and I don't know how I continued to sing, but I did so. I never
Dialogue: 0,1:02:51.71,1:02:52.71,Default,,0,0,0,,asked this before.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:52.71,1:03:01.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I've got permission to ask this. That was indeed an angelic being. So, yes, an angelic
Dialogue: 0,1:03:01.34,1:03:10.70,Default,,0,0,0,,voice. It's a stunning beauty. Later on, I joined the Great Lakes Naval Choir. In World
Dialogue: 0,1:03:10.70,1:03:21.56,Default,,0,0,0,,War II, I signed up for the Navy. I forget how I became an atheist. Somehow or other.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:21.56,1:03:22.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:22.56,1:03:23.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So, then, about age 13.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:23.56,1:03:24.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:24.50,1:03:30.78,Default,,0,0,0,,In the way out in the sticks of Wisconsin. I had the longest paper route in Wisconsin,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:30.78,1:03:36.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and 18 miles every day, 10 below zero on the bicycle. And in a very high storm one day,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:36.63,1:03:40.13,Default,,0,0,0,,a very high storm. It was 10 below zero. I mean, it was ferocious. All my papers are
Dialogue: 0,1:03:40.13,1:03:45.59,Default,,0,0,0,,blown away, and it's pitch black out. There isn't any light of a farmhouse for miles ahead
Dialogue: 0,1:03:45.59,1:03:52.30,Default,,0,0,0,,yet. And to get out of this cold, I dug a hole in the snow. Well, the banks in the Wisconsin
Dialogue: 0,1:03:52.30,1:03:53.82,Default,,0,0,0,,highways are probably 15 feet high by the end of the day. And I was in the middle of
Dialogue: 0,1:03:53.82,1:03:54.82,Default,,0,0,0,,the snow. I was in the middle of the snow. I was in the middle of the snow. I was in
Dialogue: 0,1:03:54.82,1:04:00.32,Default,,0,0,0,,the winter, around late winter. So, I broke through the crust of the snow, and I made
Dialogue: 0,1:04:00.32,1:04:05.31,Default,,0,0,0,,a little cave, and I climbed into the cave to get out of the wind, get of the wind.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:05.31,1:04:22.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And as soon as I got out of the wind, all of a sudden a state of infinite presence.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:22.77,1:04:34.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything became silent beyond all time. That which I am existed before all time, before
Dialogue: 0,1:04:34.78,1:04:37.74,Default,,0,0,0,,all worlds, and will exist beyond all
Dialogue: 0,1:04:38.10,1:04:47.80,Default,,0,0,0,,all worlds. That which I am was before all worlds resist and will be after all worlds
Dialogue: 0,1:04:47.80,1:04:55.84,Default,,0,0,0,,resist. That knowingness of foreverness. And I understood then, not intellectually, but
Dialogue: 0,1:04:55.84,1:05:02.34,Default,,0,0,0,,the experience of timelessness. That which has no beginning has no ending. The sense
Dialogue: 0,1:05:02.34,1:05:14.36,Default,,0,0,0,,of love was overwhelming. It's an infinite presence of the Self with a capital S. People
Dialogue: 0,1:05:14.36,1:05:19.08,Default,,0,0,0,,say, how do I know I'm enlightened? Because the presence wipes out everything. There's
Dialogue: 0,1:05:19.08,1:05:28.11,Default,,0,0,0,,no thought, there's nothing. There's only in that which you are, is that, is not different
Dialogue: 0,1:05:28.11,1:05:48.72,Default,,0,0,0,,than what you are. That moment, all fear of death disappeared forever, which was handy
Dialogue: 0,1:05:48.72,1:05:56.92,Default,,0,0,0,,in World War II, when you're about to get blown up. About to get blown up. Yes?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:56.92,1:06:03.21,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll, we'll quit with the World War II. Yeah. You're about to get blown up any second.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:03.21,1:06:06.83,Default,,0,0,0,,So I can remember, here's this mine right there, and these big things are sticking off
Dialogue: 0,1:06:06.83,1:06:12.39,Default,,0,0,0,,this mine, and it's about to bump against the ship. And this, this guy's supposed to
Dialogue: 0,1:06:12.39,1:06:15.09,Default,,0,0,0,,help me. We're supposed to keep this mine from hitting the ship, because they're all
Dialogue: 0,1:06:15.09,1:06:23.01,Default,,0,0,0,,going to blow up. He says, so, what if it blows up? I said, well, then we die. He said,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:23.01,1:06:28.63,Default,,0,0,0,,oh, you're right. And that was the end of the fear.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:28.87,1:06:35.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Total acceptance of death, then. Now, as if you want to evolve rapidly, handle death
Dialogue: 0,1:06:35.48,1:06:39.26,Default,,0,0,0,,right in the beginning. Don't leave it to the end. You decide I'll wait until I'm 85,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:39.26,1:06:44.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and then I'll face that one. Do it right now. Because underneath all the negative feelings
Dialogue: 0,1:06:44.94,1:06:50.68,Default,,0,0,0,,you see from consciousness level below 200, underneath all of them is death. So if you
Dialogue: 0,1:06:50.68,1:06:55.46,Default,,0,0,0,,start with death, if I'm not successful, then what? Then I'll be poor. And if you're poor,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:55.46,1:06:58.90,Default,,0,0,0,,then what? Then I won't be able to afford what I need. Yes. And then what? And then
Dialogue: 0,1:06:58.90,1:06:58.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be poor. And if you're poor, then what? Then I won't be able to afford what I need.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:58.94,1:07:05.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I will die. You'll find that every one of them ends up, and then I'll die. So start
Dialogue: 0,1:07:05.08,1:07:17.04,Default,,0,0,0,,by dying and get that over with. How many people here have been out of body? Yep, great.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:17.04,1:07:22.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Near death experiences. Yep, very good. All right, so people who have near death experiences
Dialogue: 0,1:07:22.66,1:07:28.20,Default,,0,0,0,,or out of body experiences are better prepared to die because you've experienced that you
Dialogue: 0,1:07:28.20,1:07:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,are, even though the body's laying there. In fact, it's odd. When you're out of the
Dialogue: 0,1:07:32.96,1:07:39.68,Default,,0,0,0,,body, the body looks totally uninteresting. It looks really stupid, and you have to get
Dialogue: 0,1:07:39.68,1:07:46.08,Default,,0,0,0,,back in it because you're not karmically free to go yet. But I can remember looking at it
Dialogue: 0,1:07:46.08,1:07:51.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and thinking, man, that is really not too attractive. I went back in it upside down,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:51.96,1:07:56.32,Default,,0,0,0,,looked at the floor through the back of my skull, had to pull myself out of the body
Dialogue: 0,1:07:56.32,1:07:57.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and re-dock.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:58.30,1:08:08.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's a good place that we're going to take a break. I was telling you my sad tale
Dialogue: 0,1:08:08.69,1:08:17.82,Default,,0,0,0,,of, let's see, where was I? World War II, I think. Anyway, I was very, as I say, spiritually
Dialogue: 0,1:08:17.82,1:08:25.32,Default,,0,0,0,,oriented. And one day, the war was over, one day walking around in the woods thinking of
Dialogue: 0,1:08:25.32,1:08:33.26,Default,,0,0,0,,nothing at all, not thinking of anything. All of a sudden, out of nowhere, came an infinite
Dialogue: 0,1:08:33.54,1:08:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,knowingness of infinite dimension of the totality of the suffering of all of mankind
Dialogue: 0,1:08:39.00,1:08:46.98,Default,,0,0,0,,since the beginning, since the beginning. The totality of the suffering of all of mankind
Dialogue: 0,1:08:46.98,1:08:56.70,Default,,0,0,0,,was like a presentation, a knowingness that came upon me. It was so overwhelming. I thought,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:57.24,1:09:05.38,Default,,0,0,0,,any God who could allow this, I want nothing to do with, and I became an atheist. From
Dialogue: 0,1:09:05.38,1:09:09.54,Default,,0,0,0,,an intensely religious point of view, I became an atheist. I became an atheist. I became
Dialogue: 0,1:09:09.56,1:09:15.71,Default,,0,0,0,,a person, I became a devoted atheist. Any God who could allow that quantity of suffering
Dialogue: 0,1:09:15.71,1:09:23.15,Default,,0,0,0,,was no God in my book. And I rejected God and I became an atheist. So, that time I was
Dialogue: 0,1:09:23.15,1:09:29.61,Default,,0,0,0,,going to a Jesuit university and I got straight A in everything. I didn't believe a word of
Dialogue: 0,1:09:29.61,1:09:35.55,Default,,0,0,0,,it. I got a straight A in the subject, you know. Why? Because if you're going to argue
Dialogue: 0,1:09:35.55,1:09:40.76,Default,,0,0,0,,against something, you better know a great deal about it. The critics of my own work,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:40.94,1:09:44.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I have that feeling. They don't know anything about it, so what they say is babbling, but
Dialogue: 0,1:09:44.20,1:09:49.96,Default,,0,0,0,,anyway, you've got to understand everything about it. So, I got straight A in all those
Dialogue: 0,1:09:49.96,1:09:59.41,Default,,0,0,0,,things. But there had to be some inner essence of truth, and therefore, I devoted myself
Dialogue: 0,1:09:59.41,1:10:06.32,Default,,0,0,0,,to the search for the essence of truth without God. I studied Buddhism and all kinds of things.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:06.32,1:10:13.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I belonged to the first Zen Institute in New York. Actually, I finally became a consultant
Dialogue: 0,1:10:13.09,1:10:13.47,Default,,0,0,0,,to
Dialogue: 0,1:10:13.53,1:10:19.52,Default,,0,0,0,,all kinds of religious orders, Catholic orders, Protestant, Episcopal Diocese, and the Zen
Dialogue: 0,1:10:19.52,1:10:28.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Monastery upstate New York, because I had, by that time, some rather profound experiences.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:28.53,1:10:35.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And I could discern whether the person was in a catatonic state or a Samadhi. I forgot
Dialogue: 0,1:10:35.04,1:10:43.49,Default,,0,0,0,,how it all went. But in the search for truth then became an obsession. And if the essence
Dialogue: 0,1:10:43.49,1:10:45.23,Default,,0,0,0,,of truth wasn't God, then what was it?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:45.23,1:10:55.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, I went to the very core of the source of consciousness itself. The exploration took
Dialogue: 0,1:10:55.95,1:11:06.75,Default,,0,0,0,,me through really Dante's inferno. It eventually took me to the levels of hell. And the levels
Dialogue: 0,1:11:06.75,1:11:15.51,Default,,0,0,0,,of hell are far beyond that which can be imagined, far more dreadful, far more worse. You enter
Dialogue: 0,1:11:15.51,1:11:22.11,Default,,0,0,0,,finally a realm, and Dante understood it. I don't know how Dante knew it. There's a
Dialogue: 0,1:11:22.11,1:11:22.23,Default,,0,0,0,,level of hell that you can't really imagine. You enter a realm, and you have to take it.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:22.23,1:11:22.25,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a level of hell that you can't really imagine. There's a level of hell that you can't
Dialogue: 0,1:11:22.25,1:11:31.88,Default,,0,0,0,,of hell where abandon all hope you enter here because you then enter a state of
Dialogue: 0,1:11:31.88,1:11:39.84,Default,,0,0,0,,timelessness so you were like damned you were cut off into hopelessness and
Dialogue: 0,1:11:39.84,1:11:46.54,Default,,0,0,0,,despair forever and you get what forever means and that is when hell really
Dialogue: 0,1:11:46.54,1:11:55.76,Default,,0,0,0,,starts cut off forever from love from God from salvation in a state of
Dialogue: 0,1:11:55.76,1:12:05.18,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual agony from which there is no release ever so timelessness just as in
Dialogue: 0,1:12:05.18,1:12:10.82,Default,,0,0,0,,the highest states you're beyond all time in the lowest state you again go
Dialogue: 0,1:12:10.82,1:12:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,back into timelessness which is beyond all description eternal agony in the
Dialogue: 0,1:12:23.00,1:12:24.46,Default,,0,0,0,,depth of eternal agony
Dialogue: 0,1:12:24.46,1:12:36.72,Default,,0,0,0,,the atheist said if there is a God I ask him for help and then I was hit by like
Dialogue: 0,1:12:36.72,1:12:47.26,Default,,0,0,0,,a bolt of lightning all that it ever had been disappeared and instead what shone
Dialogue: 0,1:12:47.26,1:13:05.66,Default,,0,0,0,,forth was the glory divinity as existence itself the whole world became
Dialogue: 0,1:13:05.66,1:13:11.84,Default,,0,0,0,,radiant with exquisite beauty to which it has remained except you get
Dialogue: 0,1:13:11.84,1:13:16.26,Default,,0,0,0,,used to it because otherwise you can't function and I'm having difficulty
Dialogue: 0,1:13:16.26,1:13:27.32,Default,,0,0,0,,functioning this morning because of the state is very close again so glad you
Dialogue: 0,1:13:27.32,1:13:34.72,Default,,0,0,0,,did there help out a little bit here okay thank you the infinite states are
Dialogue: 0,1:13:34.72,1:13:43.61,Default,,0,0,0,,so past the void which is consciousness level 850 oh I know I was going to say
Dialogue: 0,1:13:43.61,1:13:45.65,Default,,0,0,0,,that the way you get to the
Dialogue: 0,1:13:45.81,1:13:51.75,Default,,0,0,0,,void which I kept going out of previous lifetimes in the void because I follow
Dialogue: 0,1:13:51.75,1:14:00.56,Default,,0,0,0,,the pathway of negation pathway of negation will eventually take you to the
Dialogue: 0,1:14:00.56,1:14:09.96,Default,,0,0,0,,void at level 850 is nothingness as the ultimate reality it is so impressive so
Dialogue: 0,1:14:09.96,1:14:15.66,Default,,0,0,0,,awesome that you are sure that this is the state of enlightenment itself
Dialogue: 0,1:14:15.66,1:14:18.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Huang Po made the same mistake and
Dialogue: 0,1:14:21.12,1:14:27.27,Default,,0,0,0,,but having been in the infinite presence in the snowbank I realized that
Dialogue: 0,1:14:27.27,1:14:36.94,Default,,0,0,0,,nothingness was devoid of something incredibly essential and therefore I
Dialogue: 0,1:14:36.94,1:14:44.15,Default,,0,0,0,,refused the void this time because the infinite reality is the overwhelming
Dialogue: 0,1:14:44.15,1:14:57.01,Default,,0,0,0,,presence of an infinite love so the nothingness of the void you reject its
Dialogue: 0,1:14:57.01,1:15:00.44,Default,,0,0,0,,reality when you get to nothingness
Dialogue: 0,1:15:00.50,1:15:09.59,Default,,0,0,0,,reject the nothingness because divinity is allness infinite love and the owning
Dialogue: 0,1:15:09.59,1:15:15.72,Default,,0,0,0,,of that takes you past the 850 and Huang Po made the same mistake when he
Dialogue: 0,1:15:15.72,1:15:21.87,Default,,0,0,0,,wrote it calibrates at 850 the path to the occlusion. Huang Po after writing that
Dialogue: 0,1:15:21.87,1:15:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,discovered his error so before he died he went to 960 I'm happy to say for Huang
Dialogue: 0,1:15:30.96,1:15:31.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Po
Dialogue: 0,1:15:33.92,1:15:39.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, that's neither here nor there, so where were we on the slides?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:39.59,1:15:46.19,Default,,0,0,0,,After that everything, oh yes, after that everything happens autonomously and you realize
Dialogue: 0,1:15:46.19,1:15:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,the narcissistic, the idea that there's a separate you that's a causal agent is the
Dialogue: 0,1:15:55.44,1:15:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,delusion that one overcomes to reach enlightenment.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:59.44,1:16:05.16,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no you that is making decisions and causing things to happen.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:05.16,1:16:09.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is happening autonomously of its own.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:09.38,1:16:12.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is continuously.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:12.14,1:16:16.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Potentiality is constantly emerging.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:16.36,1:16:23.53,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no me that decided, oh, I think I'll put my arm up in the air to make that point.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:23.53,1:16:27.47,Default,,0,0,0,,It had already happened before I noticed it was there.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:27.47,1:16:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,If you get, it's a one ten-thousandth of a second jump that you have to get on the ego.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:34.48,1:16:38.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The experiencer aspect of the ego instantly takes credit.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:38.48,1:16:42.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It says, ah, there was an I that made that decision.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:42.24,1:16:44.56,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no I that makes that decision.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:44.56,1:16:45.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:45.56,1:16:49.31,Default,,0,0,0,,What I just said is the truth, oh Lord, resist.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:49.31,1:16:53.04,Default,,0,0,0,,What I just said is the truth, oh Lord.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:53.04,1:16:57.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't swear by the Lord unless it's the absolute truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:57.67,1:17:02.77,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no personal self that's making all the decisions over which you agonize.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:02.77,1:17:07.17,Default,,0,0,0,,All of it is happening autonomously, autonomously.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:07.17,1:17:11.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The consequent of that which you are interacts with potentiality.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:11.40,1:17:16.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And out comes the decision.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:16.94,1:17:19.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I can be as free as I want.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:19.16,1:17:20.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I can do what I want.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:20.16,1:17:25.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you don't like it, then how do you like that?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:25.38,1:17:29.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Did anybody decide to say that?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:29.39,1:17:31.86,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:31.86,1:17:40.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the states of spiritual awareness, people forget to go through joy, ecstasy.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:40.74,1:17:46.44,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, they can become paralyzing.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:46.44,1:17:49.68,Default,,0,0,0,,States of extreme ecstasy can become paralyzing.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:49.68,1:17:50.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:50.80,1:17:54.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Paralyzed, you're tireless.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:54.11,1:17:56.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You can dance for hours and hours.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:56.65,1:17:58.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You can dance tirelessly.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:58.13,1:17:59.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You can dance around the clock.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:59.13,1:18:00.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You never go to the bathroom.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:00.13,1:18:03.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't need a drink of water, water, nothing.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:03.13,1:18:07.23,Default,,0,0,0,,You just go into a state.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:07.23,1:18:08.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Yep.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:08.62,1:18:11.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Ramakrishna experienced such ecstatic states.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:11.62,1:18:12.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Yep.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:12.62,1:18:17.02,Default,,0,0,0,,They calibrate around 580, 590, around in there.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:17.02,1:18:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,So you go into all these states of consciousness, and if you've heard about them before, it's
Dialogue: 0,1:18:23.20,1:18:28.91,Default,,0,0,0,,helpful because you don't feel strange, you don't feel like something is unusual or there's
Dialogue: 0,1:18:28.91,1:18:30.61,Default,,0,0,0,,something wrong.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:30.61,1:18:34.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You say, oh, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:34.07,1:18:35.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It's okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:35.07,1:18:38.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It's okay for that to be what it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:38.22,1:18:40.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So we'll go back to the academics.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:40.44,1:18:48.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought I'd just make a few personal remarks to break up the monotony here.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:48.75,1:18:51.70,Default,,0,0,0,,As I said, no.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:51.70,1:18:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:52.80,1:18:53.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:53.80,1:18:54.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:54.80,1:19:00.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, the Kundalini energy is an actual spiritual energy.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:00.03,1:19:04.25,Default,,0,0,0,,People below 200, you realize, have sort of a group karma.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:04.25,1:19:12.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's only from 200 and up that you develop an etheric body, an etheric brain.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:12.44,1:19:16.30,Default,,0,0,0,,That seems unfair.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:16.30,1:19:19.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You only develop an etheric brain when consciousness level 200 exists.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:19.78,1:19:22.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Below 200, people don't have an etheric brain yet.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:22.86,1:19:25.20,Default,,0,0,0,,So you want them to understand spiritual concepts.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:25.20,1:19:35.57,Default,,0,0,0,,When they don't have the equipment, you can't understand that goodwill is more important
Dialogue: 0,1:19:35.57,1:19:37.87,Default,,0,0,0,,than killing and getting even.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:37.87,1:19:44.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't make any sense until you get to level 200, and then you say, oh yes, that's
Dialogue: 0,1:19:44.23,1:19:46.81,Default,,0,0,0,,obvious, that's obvious.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:46.81,1:19:50.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not obvious below 200.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:50.46,1:19:55.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody who gives up their life for another is stupid below 200, you see.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:55.02,1:20:00.82,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so, below consciousness level 200, left brain dominance, you're living in
Dialogue: 0,1:20:00.82,1:20:12.71,Default,,0,0,0,,a linear world, fight or flight, the alarm reaction, the thymus gland, the acupuncture
Dialogue: 0,1:20:12.71,1:20:16.55,Default,,0,0,0,,meridians, everything is now controlled by the left brain.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:16.55,1:20:20.51,Default,,0,0,0,,You notice in the left brain, animal world, people below 200.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:20.51,1:20:21.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's the input.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:21.51,1:20:28.29,Default,,0,0,0,,The relay is very fast to the emotional center, the thalamus, very fast to the emotional
Dialogue: 0,1:20:28.29,1:20:28.41,Default,,0,0,0,,center.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:28.41,1:20:31.71,Default,,0,0,0,,The amygdala, the hippocampus, your memory.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:31.71,1:20:37.29,Default,,0,0,0,,So your memory is of a fearful, frightening, angry, embarrassing.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:37.29,1:20:40.29,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a negative viewpoint of the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:40.29,1:20:46.91,Default,,0,0,0,,From 200 down, hate, anger, greed, selfishness, jealousy, envy, dominate.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:46.91,1:20:55.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is the world of the animal pack, and if you watch international political maneuverings,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:55.09,1:20:59.89,Default,,0,0,0,,it's no different at all than a wolf pack.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:59.89,1:21:06.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Alpha male, jostling for alpha male, constantly pushing for more territory.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:06.11,1:21:10.19,Default,,0,0,0,,You urinate on all these bushes over here, and once you're there, come over.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:10.19,1:21:18.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you do, oh, so you see that primarily the world lives on an animal level.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:18.22,1:21:23.14,Default,,0,0,0,,More and more dominance of more and more territory, so you're the alpha male, and you can have
Dialogue: 0,1:21:23.14,1:21:27.40,Default,,0,0,0,,all the alpha females, and if you're lucky, you can do this for eternity.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:27.40,1:21:30.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Boy, how boring it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:30.28,1:21:36.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Imagine that heaven where all you do is fornicate all day.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:36.20,1:21:41.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, century after century, you say, God, how am I going to have to keep fornicating?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:41.83,1:21:45.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm tired of beautiful females, so I have to keep doing it.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:45.99,1:21:53.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you wanted to do it, man, so, I mean, you know, hysterical.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:53.63,1:22:00.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Life is one eternal orgasm, isn't that hysterical?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:00.46,1:22:02.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Over 200, you give up eternal orgasm.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:02.98,1:22:05.18,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a fantasy.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:05.18,1:22:06.18,Default,,0,0,0,,What happened to our...
Dialogue: 0,1:22:06.18,1:22:14.25,Default,,0,0,0,,God's either pleased or not pleased, I don't know what it was.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:14.25,1:22:16.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, he's pleased, okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:16.33,1:22:20.07,Default,,0,0,0,,The kundalini begins to follow up the chakra system, you see?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:20.07,1:22:26.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Now right brain dominance, now context, the nonlinear domain, meaning and significance.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:26.86,1:22:32.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Your brain puts out endorphins instead of adrenaline, positive emotions, the thymus
Dialogue: 0,1:22:32.34,1:22:35.54,Default,,0,0,0,,gland, increased killer cells, so you're less prone to diseases.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:35.54,1:22:36.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Increased blood pressure.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:36.54,1:22:40.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Increased healing, balancing the acupuncture system.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:40.59,1:22:44.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And the track to the emotions is now slowed down.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:44.53,1:22:50.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So the more enlightened person, 200 and up, you get a fast track through the etheric brain,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:50.82,1:22:56.29,Default,,0,0,0,,which is the capacity to see the essence of a thing, very fast, through the emotional
Dialogue: 0,1:22:56.29,1:23:00.97,Default,,0,0,0,,center, and your memory is of a very wonderful and positive experience.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:00.97,1:23:01.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:01.97,1:23:05.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I experienced this audience, it was very wonderful and positive, you know, period.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:05.97,1:23:08.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Experience.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:08.71,1:23:12.10,Default,,0,0,0,,That's because I see the essence of things.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:12.10,1:23:18.70,Default,,0,0,0,,So obviously, an audience like this calibrates over 200, so I pick up the positive essence
Dialogue: 0,1:23:18.70,1:23:23.14,Default,,0,0,0,,of this audience, and you feel happy and content because you're surrounded by that which is
Dialogue: 0,1:23:23.14,1:23:28.13,Default,,0,0,0,,safety and loving, supportive, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:28.13,1:23:32.03,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so we'll move on.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:32.03,1:23:35.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I just wanted to point out that there's an actual physiologic difference.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:35.95,1:23:38.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the rates of enlightenment...
Dialogue: 0,1:23:38.20,1:23:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Or happiness, let's say.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:42.40,1:23:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,If we start at the bottom, calibrated at level 20, the number...
Dialogue: 0,1:23:46.48,1:23:50.62,Default,,0,0,0,,The percent of people who are happy at these various consciousness levels.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:50.62,1:23:56.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So happiness is not a consequence of the world and what you have in the world and what you
Dialogue: 0,1:23:56.16,1:23:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,do in the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:59.00,1:24:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Happiness is a consequence of that which you have become.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:03.28,1:24:11.01,Default,,0,0,0,,If you have become this, then the likelihood of happiness is close to 70%.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:11.01,1:24:20.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Happiness, then, is not a socio-economic class or political trauma.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:20.62,1:24:24.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a consequence of that which you have become.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:24.43,1:24:31.02,Default,,0,0,0,,When you become the fulfillment of your potential, you're happy no matter what.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:31.02,1:24:34.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You're happy no matter what.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:34.52,1:24:38.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So at this low level, these are criminal populations here, criminal populations.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:38.80,1:24:44.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, at log 20, only 1% of people are happy.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:44.40,1:24:45.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:45.40,1:24:46.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:46.36,1:24:47.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:47.74,1:24:52.92,Default,,0,0,0,,People who live in the world of guilt and penance, you see, at consciousness level 30,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:52.92,1:24:58.38,Default,,0,0,0,,4% are happy.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:58.38,1:25:03.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Sackcloth and ashes was the sort of medieval way to God through Christianity.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:03.77,1:25:07.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, God, forgive me my evil and guilt.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:07.67,1:25:14.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And you kneel and crawl on your knees all the way to the cathedral, beating on yourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:14.08,1:25:17.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, you know, that's real narcissism, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:17.02,1:25:18.02,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:18.34,1:25:19.34,Default,,0,0,0,,That's real drama.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:19.34,1:25:20.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, God, I am such a sinner.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:20.34,1:25:21.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Give me a break, will you?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:21.34,1:25:22.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Wallowing in guilt and penance is sort of a medieval.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:22.34,1:25:23.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Medieval.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:23.34,1:25:24.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's one of the reasons I gave up Christianity when I became an atheist.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:24.34,1:25:25.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn't see wallowing in guilt and penance.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:25.34,1:25:27.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, you know, if man can't tell truth from falsehood, I mean, whatever happened
Dialogue: 0,1:25:27.14,1:25:28.14,Default,,0,0,0,,in the Garden of Eden, I mean, I don't have anything to do with it.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:28.14,1:25:29.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, I don't have anything to do with it.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:29.14,1:25:30.14,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:30.14,1:25:31.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:31.14,1:25:32.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:32.14,1:25:33.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:33.14,1:25:34.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:34.24,1:25:35.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:35.24,1:25:36.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:36.24,1:25:37.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:37.24,1:25:38.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:38.24,1:25:39.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:39.24,1:25:40.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:40.24,1:25:45.72,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, if man can't tell truth from falsehood, I mean, whatever happened in the
Dialogue: 0,1:25:45.72,1:25:52.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Garden, you know, of Eden, I mean, I don't have anything to do with it.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:52.51,1:25:54.51,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:54.51,1:25:55.43,Default,,0,0,0,,My toy, you know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:55.43,1:26:02.99,Default,,0,0,0,,The serpent took advantage of the fact that the human mind, unaided, is unable to discern
Dialogue: 0,1:26:02.99,1:26:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,,truth from falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:05.68,1:26:08.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Unaided.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:08.67,1:26:12.71,Default,,0,0,0,,The human mind, by virtue of its structure.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:12.71,1:26:20.78,Default,,0,0,0,,cannot tell appearance from essence. Socrates said it. All men choose only the good. A lot
Dialogue: 0,1:26:20.78,1:26:25.38,Default,,0,0,0,,of times we feel guilty because we find it difficult to forgive somebody. See? Christ
Dialogue: 0,1:26:25.38,1:26:29.84,Default,,0,0,0,,said forgive them all, they know not what they do, etc. The Buddha said the only difficulty
Dialogue: 0,1:26:29.84,1:26:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,with everyone is ignorance. So you remind yourself of that profound innate ignorance.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:36.32,1:26:44.23,Default,,0,0,0,,That's built into the ego structure as it evolved. The ego is unable to discern appearance
Dialogue: 0,1:26:44.23,1:26:49.77,Default,,0,0,0,,from essence. It's only consciousness level 600, the opening of the third eye of the Buddhic
Dialogue: 0,1:26:49.77,1:26:58.11,Default,,0,0,0,,body, the third body, that one discerns essence rather than appearance. So the value of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:26:58.11,1:27:04.19,Default,,0,0,0,,calibration is you can accomplish what the human mind cannot do. The human mind looks
Dialogue: 0,1:27:04.19,1:27:09.73,Default,,0,0,0,,at a thing, it doesn't know whether that's gold or fool's gold. Instantly with kinesiology
Dialogue: 0,1:27:09.73,1:27:13.69,Default,,0,0,0,,you know what it is. So it bypasses. All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:14.68,1:27:14.94,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:14.94,1:27:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:14.96,1:27:14.98,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:14.98,1:27:15.04,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:15.04,1:27:15.06,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:15.06,1:27:15.08,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:15.08,1:27:15.14,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:15.14,1:27:15.16,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:15.16,1:27:15.26,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:15.26,1:27:15.28,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:15.28,1:27:15.30,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:15.30,1:27:15.32,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:15.32,1:27:15.48,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:15.48,1:27:15.56,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:15.56,1:27:15.58,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:15.58,1:27:16.20,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:16.20,1:27:16.24,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:16.24,1:27:16.32,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:16.32,1:27:16.36,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:16.36,1:27:16.42,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:16.42,1:27:16.50,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:16.78,1:27:23.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Only 5% say they're happy. Those who live in fear, 10%. Those who are angry,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:24.22,1:27:29.81,Default,,0,0,0,,only 12% of those people are happy. And they're probably retarded or something, but anyway.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:31.57,1:27:40.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Pride at least makes sense. Log 175, 22%. That makes sense, you know. At least you're
Dialogue: 0,1:27:40.30,1:27:46.10,Default,,0,0,0,,happy that you're better than other people and all that. Everybody secretly believes
Dialogue: 0,1:27:46.10,1:27:49.34,Default,,0,0,0,,that their view of reality is correct and everybody else's is wrong.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:49.66,1:27:50.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't we all?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:52.10,1:27:54.72,Default,,0,0,0,,All in favor of I'm right and everybody else is wrong.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:55.02,1:27:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Yay, good.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:58.90,1:28:01.24,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't get rid of the ego unless you own it.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:01.84,1:28:03.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, the narcissistic core of the ego.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:04.18,1:28:05.98,Default,,0,0,0,,It just loves being right.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:06.98,1:28:10.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's willing to be right even if it costs you your life.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:10.22,1:28:10.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:12.77,1:28:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,When you get beyond pride.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:15.98,1:28:18.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So we know that pride is where so many things fall.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:20.07,1:28:23.45,Default,,0,0,0,,It's where all the great dictators, if they aren't crazy,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:23.59,1:28:25.91,Default,,0,0,0,,before they get there, they're crazy after they get there.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:26.43,1:28:32.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of the pride, the narcissistic ego just goes crazy.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:33.96,1:28:37.22,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, at 200 is the capacity to tell the truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:37.90,1:28:39.88,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the first in the 12-step groups.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:39.88,1:28:40.82,Default,,0,0,0,,That's step one.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:41.56,1:28:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,We admitted we were powerless over something.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:43.92,1:28:45.52,Default,,0,0,0,,What? Admitted you were powerless over?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:45.72,1:28:47.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow, what an affront to the ego.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:47.36,1:28:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The ego isn't going to admit it's powerless.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:49.62,1:28:51.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It's going to admit it's powerless over anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:51.50,1:28:54.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It's going to control it and make it different this time.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:54.25,1:28:56.95,Default,,0,0,0,,At 200, then you enter the world of honesty.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:58.76,1:29:03.26,Default,,0,0,0,,At level 200, 55% of people are happy.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:04.41,1:29:07.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And neutrality, you move beyond courage.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:07.71,1:29:12.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Neutrality is it's okay if it happens this way and it's okay if it happens that way.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:12.57,1:29:14.40,Default,,0,0,0,,If I get the job, it's great.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:14.40,1:29:15.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And if I don't, I'll get another job.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:15.94,1:29:17.58,Default,,0,0,0,,So neutral is very comfortable.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:18.28,1:29:21.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It's fun being with neutral people because they're easygoing.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:21.44,1:29:23.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And 60% of them are happy.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:23.88,1:29:24.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:25.53,1:29:28.31,Default,,0,0,0,,The other 40% have bad spouses or something.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:28.31,1:29:28.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:28.55,1:29:32.85,Default,,0,0,0,,There's some defect in this.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:32.85,1:29:36.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Because if you're really at neutral, you'd be happy under any circumstance.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:36.95,1:29:38.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So we'll have to reexamine that.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:39.31,1:29:41.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been in neutral and it's okay, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:42.17,1:29:44.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, like I say, a bomb is about to go off.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:44.03,1:29:45.65,Default,,0,0,0,,The mine is about to explode.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:45.65,1:29:48.45,Default,,0,0,0,,And it goes off, it goes off.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:48.45,1:29:50.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So if it doesn't, it doesn't.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:51.55,1:29:52.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So what's the big deal?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:52.69,1:29:56.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Either die or you don't.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:56.42,1:30:04.27,Default,,0,0,0,,So willingness is a positive attitude at 310, but 68% of the people,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:04.27,1:30:08.05,Default,,0,0,0,,these are the people that help make the world, they're humanitarians.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:08.63,1:30:12.93,Default,,0,0,0,,They sign up for all kinds of help things, clean up Katrina after Katrina,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:12.93,1:30:13.73,Default,,0,0,0,,all these kind of things.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:14.84,1:30:22.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Acceptance is the beginning of the only owning of your power at 350, 71%.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:23.61,1:30:24.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Reason is the world of the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:24.77,1:30:25.77,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the world of the intellect.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:25.77,1:30:29.27,Default,,0,0,0,,We didn't do the great books of the Western world, did we?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:29.27,1:30:30.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we'll have to do them.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:30.90,1:30:38.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Reason now is the beginning of the advances of Western civilization as we understand it,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:38.10,1:30:39.90,Default,,0,0,0,,is the level of the 400s.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:39.90,1:30:43.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The great books of the Western world are at the 400s.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:45.56,1:30:48.90,Default,,0,0,0,,On the slide, see if you can find the great books of the Western world.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:48.90,1:30:50.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And we'll just flick to it later on.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:51.67,1:30:53.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, it's the intellectual backbone.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:53.37,1:30:54.38,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the intellectual backbone.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:54.38,1:30:55.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the intellectual backbone.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:55.54,1:31:02.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the intellectual backbone of Western civilization begins with Plato, Aristotle.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:02.08,1:31:09.56,Default,,0,0,0,,To my viewpoint, the highest evolution of human civilization was around 350 BC,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:09.56,1:31:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's been downhill ever since, frankly.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:18.96,1:31:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,To forgive everybody is easy if you accept Socrates' wisdom.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:22.96,1:31:29.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone chooses only the good, you know, what they think to be the good.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:29.72,1:31:31.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So, everyone is only choosing what they...
Dialogue: 0,1:31:31.72,1:31:35.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you see the innocence that they think that will bring them fame and happiness and,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:35.72,1:31:41.43,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, whatever they do, which is outrageous on television.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:41.43,1:31:43.43,Default,,0,0,0,,But if, you know...
Dialogue: 0,1:31:43.43,1:31:48.29,Default,,0,0,0,,So, anyway, neutrality, it's okay if it goes this way.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:48.29,1:31:52.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Willingness is joining in, and acceptance is even higher.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:52.29,1:31:58.29,Default,,0,0,0,,And reason is the intellect, and this is the bulwark of the Western world.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:58.29,1:32:00.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The 400s then takes you through the great books.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:01.61,1:32:04.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The great books of the Western world.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:04.64,1:32:07.64,Default,,0,0,0,,In all the ones that I studied, it used to be in college,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:07.64,1:32:09.64,Default,,0,0,0,,you studied the great books of the Western world.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:09.64,1:32:11.64,Default,,0,0,0,,That was a liberal education.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:11.64,1:32:16.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Nowadays, they avoid anything that's in the 400s.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:16.64,1:32:20.74,Default,,0,0,0,,They stick to 190 or something.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:20.74,1:32:25.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, relativism coverage is about 190.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:25.08,1:32:28.08,Default,,0,0,0,,So, where were we on the chart?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:28.08,1:32:29.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, there they are.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:29.08,1:32:30.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:30.12,1:32:31.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So, there's all...
Dialogue: 0,1:32:31.12,1:32:32.12,Default,,0,0,0,,These are all the friends of my childhood.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:33.12,1:32:35.12,Default,,0,0,0,,They were my friends, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:35.12,1:32:37.12,Default,,0,0,0,,because that was a small ectomorph,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:37.12,1:32:40.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and the coach wouldn't allow me on the field.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:40.12,1:32:42.12,Default,,0,0,0,,He said, your bones are going to get all broken.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:42.12,1:32:44.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The doctor wouldn't give an okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:44.12,1:32:46.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I read, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:46.12,1:32:48.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I was skinny with thick glasses
Dialogue: 0,1:32:48.12,1:32:51.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and sat in a big chair and read books.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:53.12,1:32:55.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So, these are all my pals from childhood,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:55.12,1:32:57.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and when I get back on the other side,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:57.12,1:33:00.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm looking forward to hanging out with them again.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:01.12,1:33:03.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Socrates and Plato and all the folks.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:03.12,1:33:07.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So, anyway, these are the great books of the rest of the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:07.50,1:33:11.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Aristophanes, Aristotle, 498.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:11.50,1:33:13.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Augustine, Marcus Aurelius.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:13.53,1:33:15.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The aphorisms of Marcus Aurelius.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:15.53,1:33:16.53,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what I'm reading as a child,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:16.53,1:33:18.53,Default,,0,0,0,,the aphorisms of Marcus Aurelius.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:18.53,1:33:20.53,Default,,0,0,0,,But then normal childhood, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:20.53,1:33:21.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I kind of think of it, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:24.60,1:33:25.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Descartes, of course, is brilliant
Dialogue: 0,1:33:25.60,1:33:27.60,Default,,0,0,0,,because he pointed out the difference
Dialogue: 0,1:33:27.60,1:33:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,between res interna and res externa.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:29.60,1:33:31.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The world as you see it
Dialogue: 0,1:33:31.82,1:33:32.82,Default,,0,0,0,,as compared to the world as you see it,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:32.82,1:33:35.92,Default,,0,0,0,,as compared to the world the way it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:35.92,1:33:36.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:36.92,1:33:38.92,Default,,0,0,0,,To go beyond appearance, which is illusion,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:38.92,1:33:41.14,Default,,0,0,0,,to reality, which is essence.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:41.14,1:33:44.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And until we had consciousness calibration,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:44.14,1:33:46.14,Default,,0,0,0,,there was frankly no way to do that.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:46.14,1:33:48.14,Default,,0,0,0,,There was no way you could tell the essence of a thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:48.14,1:33:50.14,Default,,0,0,0,,All you had was the appearance.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:50.14,1:33:53.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So, Descartes.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:55.48,1:33:56.48,Default,,0,0,0,,What was it?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:56.48,1:33:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I forgot what I put this up for.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:58.48,1:34:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,These are, and Hegel's, of course,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:00.48,1:34:02.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The Absolute,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:02.55,1:34:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,which the relatives,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:04.55,1:34:06.55,Default,,0,0,0,,both of us have warned you about,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:06.55,1:34:09.74,Default,,0,0,0,,is 499.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:09.74,1:34:12.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Einstein was 499.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:12.74,1:34:15.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Freud, 499.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:15.74,1:34:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Carl Jung was at 520.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:18.96,1:34:21.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so this is the world Newtonian physics.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:21.96,1:34:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Plato at 485.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:25.00,1:34:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And you see all the great minds of history.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:28.00,1:34:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The great minds of history.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:29.00,1:34:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Now the last book,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:30.00,1:34:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the last book was on Freud.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:32.00,1:34:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The last book,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:33.00,1:34:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,these were collected by
Dialogue: 0,1:34:34.00,1:34:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the University of Chicago.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:36.00,1:34:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And there's only two things that stand out.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:39.00,1:34:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Karl Marx.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:40.00,1:34:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,See, they're all about 440, 460.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:43.00,1:34:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Karl Marx doesn't belong in here.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:45.00,1:34:47.06,Default,,0,0,0,,He's only, well, he's at 130.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:47.06,1:34:50.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Engels just makes it at 200.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:50.06,1:34:52.06,Default,,0,0,0,,But he's on Marx's coattails.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:52.06,1:34:54.06,Default,,0,0,0,,But all this you can see is wrong,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:54.06,1:34:55.06,Default,,0,0,0,,has been wrong with,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:55.06,1:35:00.06,Default,,0,0,0,,relativism really is a variation of Marxism.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:00.06,1:35:03.06,Default,,0,0,0,,So to drop from 450 to 130,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:03.06,1:35:05.06,Default,,0,0,0,,if you establish Marxism as a,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:05.06,1:35:07.06,Default,,0,0,0,,as a cultural reality,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:07.06,1:35:09.06,Default,,0,0,0,,you end up as Mayo did in China
Dialogue: 0,1:35:09.06,1:35:11.06,Default,,0,0,0,,with 30 million people starving to death.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:11.06,1:35:13.06,Default,,0,0,0,,30 million people starving to death.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:13.06,1:35:14.06,Default,,0,0,0,,In North Korea,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:14.06,1:35:16.06,Default,,0,0,0,,tens of millions starve to death.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:16.06,1:35:18.06,Default,,0,0,0,,So Marxism hasn't worked out.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:18.06,1:35:21.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It leads to the masses starving to death.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:23.96,1:35:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,But he was important politically.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:24.96,1:35:25.96,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why he's put in
Dialogue: 0,1:35:25.96,1:35:27.96,Default,,0,0,0,,the great books of the Western world.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:27.96,1:35:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So we'll go back to the slides
Dialogue: 0,1:35:28.96,1:35:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,of what we were doing.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:30.96,1:35:33.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Here you see reason,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:33.88,1:35:35.88,Default,,0,0,0,,a reasonable person,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:35.88,1:35:36.88,Default,,0,0,0,,reasonable person,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:36.88,1:35:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,has an 80% chance.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:38.88,1:35:39.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Love at 500,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:39.88,1:35:41.88,Default,,0,0,0,,only 89% are happy.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:41.88,1:35:43.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know what's the matter with them.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:45.88,1:35:46.88,Default,,0,0,0,,What more than love do you want?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:46.88,1:35:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know what's the matter with those people.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:48.88,1:35:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll have to examine some of these people,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:50.88,1:35:51.88,Default,,0,0,0,,holdbacks here.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:51.88,1:35:52.88,Default,,0,0,0,,They're peculiar.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:52.88,1:35:53.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe they're not all there or something.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:53.88,1:35:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:55.92,1:35:57.92,Default,,0,0,0,,At 540,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:57.92,1:36:00.92,Default,,0,0,0,,love becomes unconditional.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:00.92,1:36:02.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The 12-step groups calibrate at 540.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:02.92,1:36:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,,540.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:03.92,1:36:04.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:04.92,1:36:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,one of the great ways to God
Dialogue: 0,1:36:05.92,1:36:07.11,Default,,0,0,0,,is through the 12-step programs,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:07.11,1:36:08.11,Default,,0,0,0,,of course,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:08.11,1:36:09.11,Default,,0,0,0,,the miracles,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:09.11,1:36:10.11,Default,,0,0,0,,other things,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:10.11,1:36:11.11,Default,,0,0,0,,other than,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:11.11,1:36:12.11,Default,,0,0,0,,because not everybody finds religion,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:12.11,1:36:13.11,Default,,0,0,0,,you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:13.11,1:36:14.11,Default,,0,0,0,,acceptable.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:14.11,1:36:15.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So they say,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:15.11,1:36:16.11,Default,,0,0,0,,well,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:16.11,1:36:17.11,Default,,0,0,0,,how can I,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:17.11,1:36:18.11,Default,,0,0,0,,you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:18.11,1:36:19.11,Default,,0,0,0,,transcend and get somewhere
Dialogue: 0,1:36:19.11,1:36:20.11,Default,,0,0,0,,without going to church
Dialogue: 0,1:36:20.11,1:36:21.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and being a religionist?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:21.11,1:36:22.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The 12-step groups.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:22.11,1:36:23.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Unconditional love means
Dialogue: 0,1:36:23.11,1:36:24.11,Default,,0,0,0,,forgiving people
Dialogue: 0,1:36:24.11,1:36:25.11,Default,,0,0,0,,no matter what.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:25.11,1:36:26.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And you can't forgive them
Dialogue: 0,1:36:26.11,1:36:27.11,Default,,0,0,0,,if you don't love them.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:27.11,1:36:28.11,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't forgive them
Dialogue: 0,1:36:28.11,1:36:29.11,Default,,0,0,0,,if you don't love them.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:29.11,1:36:30.11,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't forgive them
Dialogue: 0,1:36:30.11,1:36:31.11,Default,,0,0,0,,if you don't love them.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:31.11,1:36:32.17,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't forgive them
Dialogue: 0,1:36:32.17,1:36:33.17,Default,,0,0,0,,if you don't love them.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:33.17,1:36:34.17,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't forgive them
Dialogue: 0,1:36:34.17,1:36:35.17,Default,,0,0,0,,no matter what
Dialogue: 0,1:36:35.17,1:36:36.17,Default,,0,0,0,,unless you accept
Dialogue: 0,1:36:36.17,1:36:37.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Socrates'
Dialogue: 0,1:36:37.17,1:36:38.17,Default,,0,0,0,,understanding
Dialogue: 0,1:36:38.17,1:36:39.17,Default,,0,0,0,,that all people
Dialogue: 0,1:36:39.17,1:36:40.17,Default,,0,0,0,,only choose
Dialogue: 0,1:36:40.17,1:36:41.17,Default,,0,0,0,,what they concern
Dialogue: 0,1:36:41.17,1:36:42.17,Default,,0,0,0,,to be the good.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:42.17,1:36:43.17,Default,,0,0,0,,So now you realize
Dialogue: 0,1:36:43.17,1:36:44.17,Default,,0,0,0,,it's easy to forgive them
Dialogue: 0,1:36:44.17,1:36:45.17,Default,,0,0,0,,because what is ignorance?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:45.17,1:36:47.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Ignorance is just not knowing,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:47.17,1:36:48.17,Default,,0,0,0,,knowing essence
Dialogue: 0,1:36:48.17,1:36:49.17,Default,,0,0,0,,from appearance
Dialogue: 0,1:36:49.17,1:36:51.17,Default,,0,0,0,,for which we forgive people.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:51.17,1:36:52.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do we forgive them?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:52.17,1:36:53.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Because we see
Dialogue: 0,1:36:53.17,1:36:54.17,Default,,0,0,0,,from the evolution
Dialogue: 0,1:36:54.17,1:36:55.17,Default,,0,0,0,,of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:36:55.17,1:36:56.17,Default,,0,0,0,,that many people
Dialogue: 0,1:36:56.17,1:36:57.17,Default,,0,0,0,,have not evolved
Dialogue: 0,1:36:57.17,1:36:58.17,Default,,0,0,0,,to the capacity
Dialogue: 0,1:36:58.17,1:36:59.17,Default,,0,0,0,,where they could see
Dialogue: 0,1:36:59.17,1:37:00.17,Default,,0,0,0,,the essence of a thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:00.17,1:37:01.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:01.17,1:37:02.17,Default,,0,0,0,,you forgive them
Dialogue: 0,1:37:02.17,1:37:03.17,Default,,0,0,0,,because you realize
Dialogue: 0,1:37:03.17,1:37:04.17,Default,,0,0,0,,they haven't evolved
Dialogue: 0,1:37:04.17,1:37:05.17,Default,,0,0,0,,to that point yet.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:05.17,1:37:06.17,Default,,0,0,0,,For the same reason
Dialogue: 0,1:37:06.17,1:37:07.17,Default,,0,0,0,,we don't hate a kid
Dialogue: 0,1:37:07.17,1:37:08.17,Default,,0,0,0,,with a low IQ
Dialogue: 0,1:37:08.17,1:37:09.17,Default,,0,0,0,,because he doesn't
Dialogue: 0,1:37:09.17,1:37:10.17,Default,,0,0,0,,get straight A's.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:10.17,1:37:11.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So love becomes
Dialogue: 0,1:37:11.56,1:37:12.56,Default,,0,0,0,,unconditional
Dialogue: 0,1:37:12.56,1:37:13.56,Default,,0,0,0,,at 540,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:13.56,1:37:14.56,Default,,0,0,0,,at 570,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:14.56,1:37:15.56,Default,,0,0,0,,at sainthood.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:15.56,1:37:16.56,Default,,0,0,0,,570,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:16.56,1:37:17.56,Default,,0,0,0,,all the saints
Dialogue: 0,1:37:17.56,1:37:18.56,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrate at 570.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:18.56,1:37:19.91,Default,,0,0,0,,As I say,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:19.91,1:37:20.91,Default,,0,0,0,,the current pope
Dialogue: 0,1:37:20.91,1:37:21.91,Default,,0,0,0,,is practically
Dialogue: 0,1:37:21.91,1:37:22.91,Default,,0,0,0,,at 570
Dialogue: 0,1:37:22.91,1:37:25.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and the Buddhist fellow,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:25.91,1:37:28.28,Default,,0,0,0,,whatever his name is,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:28.28,1:37:29.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I forget.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:29.28,1:37:30.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:30.70,1:37:31.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I understand him
Dialogue: 0,1:37:31.70,1:37:32.70,Default,,0,0,0,,because he laughs
Dialogue: 0,1:37:32.70,1:37:33.70,Default,,0,0,0,,all the time.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:35.70,1:37:36.70,Default,,0,0,0,,The Dalai Lama.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:36.70,1:37:37.70,Default,,0,0,0,,The Dalai Lama,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:37.70,1:37:38.70,Default,,0,0,0,,yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:38.70,1:37:39.70,Default,,0,0,0,,There's somebody
Dialogue: 0,1:37:39.70,1:37:40.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I was talking to,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:40.70,1:37:41.70,Default,,0,0,0,,some famous person
Dialogue: 0,1:37:41.70,1:37:42.70,Default,,0,0,0,,on the phone
Dialogue: 0,1:37:42.70,1:37:43.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and I was laughing
Dialogue: 0,1:37:43.70,1:37:44.70,Default,,0,0,0,,all the time
Dialogue: 0,1:37:44.70,1:37:45.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and she was annoyed.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:45.73,1:37:46.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:46.73,1:37:47.73,Default,,0,0,0,,she doesn't understand
Dialogue: 0,1:37:47.73,1:37:48.86,Default,,0,0,0,,why I'm laughing
Dialogue: 0,1:37:48.86,1:37:49.86,Default,,0,0,0,,all the time.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:49.86,1:37:50.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I said,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:50.86,1:37:51.86,Default,,0,0,0,,well,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:51.86,1:37:52.86,Default,,0,0,0,,the same reason
Dialogue: 0,1:37:52.86,1:37:53.86,Default,,0,0,0,,the Dalai Lama
Dialogue: 0,1:37:53.86,1:37:54.86,Default,,0,0,0,,laughs all the time
Dialogue: 0,1:37:54.86,1:37:55.86,Default,,0,0,0,,because life
Dialogue: 0,1:37:55.86,1:37:57.56,Default,,0,0,0,,is a constant
Dialogue: 0,1:37:57.56,1:37:58.56,Default,,0,0,0,,hysterical comedy.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:59.95,1:38:00.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Even as the
Dialogue: 0,1:38:00.95,1:38:01.95,Default,,0,0,0,,headsman's coming over,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:01.95,1:38:02.95,Default,,0,0,0,,it's a comedy
Dialogue: 0,1:38:02.95,1:38:03.95,Default,,0,0,0,,because you realize
Dialogue: 0,1:38:03.95,1:38:04.95,Default,,0,0,0,,the whole thing
Dialogue: 0,1:38:04.95,1:38:05.95,Default,,0,0,0,,is an absurd drama.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:05.95,1:38:06.95,Default,,0,0,0,,You're laughing
Dialogue: 0,1:38:06.95,1:38:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,all the time.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:08.40,1:38:09.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Now,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:09.40,1:38:10.40,Default,,0,0,0,,peace is at 600.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:10.40,1:38:11.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Now,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:11.43,1:38:12.43,Default,,0,0,0,,this is the peace
Dialogue: 0,1:38:12.43,1:38:13.43,Default,,0,0,0,,of God.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:13.43,1:38:14.43,Default,,0,0,0,,600 is the
Dialogue: 0,1:38:14.43,1:38:15.43,Default,,0,0,0,,peace of God
Dialogue: 0,1:38:15.43,1:38:16.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and 600
Dialogue: 0,1:38:16.43,1:38:17.43,Default,,0,0,0,,is the beginning
Dialogue: 0,1:38:17.43,1:38:18.43,Default,,0,0,0,,of the levels
Dialogue: 0,1:38:18.43,1:38:19.43,Default,,0,0,0,,of enlightenment.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:19.43,1:38:20.43,Default,,0,0,0,,At 600,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:20.43,1:38:21.43,Default,,0,0,0,,you can't really
Dialogue: 0,1:38:21.43,1:38:22.43,Default,,0,0,0,,function.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:22.43,1:38:23.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't really
Dialogue: 0,1:38:23.65,1:38:24.65,Default,,0,0,0,,do anything
Dialogue: 0,1:38:24.65,1:38:25.65,Default,,0,0,0,,at 600
Dialogue: 0,1:38:25.65,1:38:26.65,Default,,0,0,0,,because
Dialogue: 0,1:38:26.65,1:38:27.65,Default,,0,0,0,,it's non-linear,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:27.65,1:38:28.65,Default,,0,0,0,,it's eternal,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:28.65,1:38:30.13,Default,,0,0,0,,it's forever
Dialogue: 0,1:38:30.13,1:38:31.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and from 600
Dialogue: 0,1:38:31.13,1:38:32.13,Default,,0,0,0,,on up,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:32.13,1:38:33.13,Default,,0,0,0,,you can leave
Dialogue: 0,1:38:33.13,1:38:34.13,Default,,0,0,0,,the world
Dialogue: 0,1:38:34.13,1:38:35.13,Default,,0,0,0,,anytime you like
Dialogue: 0,1:38:35.13,1:38:36.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's invitational.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:36.13,1:38:37.13,Default,,0,0,0,,At 600,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:37.13,1:38:38.13,Default,,0,0,0,,you realize
Dialogue: 0,1:38:38.13,1:38:39.32,Default,,0,0,0,,that you
Dialogue: 0,1:38:39.32,1:38:40.32,Default,,0,0,0,,are not
Dialogue: 0,1:38:40.32,1:38:42.03,Default,,0,0,0,,that
Dialogue: 0,1:38:42.03,1:38:43.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and the state
Dialogue: 0,1:38:43.03,1:38:44.03,Default,,0,0,0,,of bliss
Dialogue: 0,1:38:44.03,1:38:46.37,Default,,0,0,0,,is
Dialogue: 0,1:38:46.37,1:38:47.82,Default,,0,0,0,,blissful.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:51.82,1:38:52.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not necessary
Dialogue: 0,1:38:52.82,1:38:53.82,Default,,0,0,0,,to continue on.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:53.82,1:38:54.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:54.82,1:38:55.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and if these states
Dialogue: 0,1:38:55.98,1:38:56.98,Default,,0,0,0,,hit you,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:56.98,1:38:57.98,Default,,0,0,0,,you can get
Dialogue: 0,1:38:57.98,1:38:58.98,Default,,0,0,0,,an okay
Dialogue: 0,1:38:58.98,1:38:59.98,Default,,0,0,0,,to leave
Dialogue: 0,1:38:59.98,1:39:00.98,Default,,0,0,0,,at any time.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:00.98,1:39:01.98,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're driving
Dialogue: 0,1:39:01.98,1:39:02.98,Default,,0,0,0,,down the highway,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:02.98,1:39:03.98,Default,,0,0,0,,it's sort of
Dialogue: 0,1:39:03.98,1:39:04.98,Default,,0,0,0,,what to do about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:04.98,1:39:05.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You know,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:05.98,1:39:06.98,Default,,0,0,0,,well,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:06.98,1:39:08.59,Default,,0,0,0,,should I pull over
Dialogue: 0,1:39:08.59,1:39:09.59,Default,,0,0,0,,or not pull over?
Dialogue: 0,1:39:09.59,1:39:10.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess I better pull over.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:10.59,1:39:11.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm trying to enjoy
Dialogue: 0,1:39:11.59,1:39:13.58,Default,,0,0,0,,the light of it,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:13.58,1:39:14.58,Default,,0,0,0,,you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:14.58,1:39:15.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And there are
Dialogue: 0,1:39:15.58,1:39:16.58,Default,,0,0,0,,very few people
Dialogue: 0,1:39:16.58,1:39:17.58,Default,,0,0,0,,at those higher levels.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:17.58,1:39:18.58,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason is
Dialogue: 0,1:39:18.58,1:39:19.64,Default,,0,0,0,,for,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:19.64,1:39:20.64,Default,,0,0,0,,at 600
Dialogue: 0,1:39:20.64,1:39:21.64,Default,,0,0,0,,you can leave
Dialogue: 0,1:39:21.64,1:39:22.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and
Dialogue: 0,1:39:22.64,1:39:23.64,Default,,0,0,0,,50%
Dialogue: 0,1:39:23.64,1:39:24.84,Default,,0,0,0,,that are
Dialogue: 0,1:39:24.84,1:39:25.84,Default,,0,0,0,,at level 600
Dialogue: 0,1:39:25.84,1:39:26.84,Default,,0,0,0,,will leave.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:26.84,1:39:28.54,Default,,0,0,0,,You have the option
Dialogue: 0,1:39:28.54,1:39:29.54,Default,,0,0,0,,to leave.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:29.54,1:39:30.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Each level,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:30.54,1:39:31.54,Default,,0,0,0,,as you advance,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:31.54,1:39:32.54,Default,,0,0,0,,again,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:32.54,1:39:33.54,Default,,0,0,0,,you have a 50%
Dialogue: 0,1:39:33.54,1:39:34.54,Default,,0,0,0,,chance to leave.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:34.54,1:39:35.54,Default,,0,0,0,,At 850,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:35.54,1:39:36.54,Default,,0,0,0,,you have it,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:36.54,1:39:37.54,Default,,0,0,0,,you can leave,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:37.54,1:39:38.67,Default,,0,0,0,,you can leave
Dialogue: 0,1:39:38.67,1:39:39.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and finally,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:39.67,1:39:40.67,Default,,0,0,0,,there's hardly anyone
Dialogue: 0,1:39:40.67,1:39:41.67,Default,,0,0,0,,left on the planet
Dialogue: 0,1:39:41.67,1:39:48.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Not because it's a rare, but because everyone leaves.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:51.71,1:39:56.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I hate to tell you, but everybody, you realize you don't have to continue on.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:57.69,1:40:05.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Some people, by virtue of some prior commitment and agreement, return to the world and function again.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:05.83,1:40:11.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Usually as teachers, and that's their agreement.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:11.08,1:40:14.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The karmic fulfillment of that potentiality.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:15.43,1:40:17.79,Default,,0,0,0,,To share what you have become with others.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:18.87,1:40:23.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And by sharing that, what you have become with others, they become their own potential.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:24.30,1:40:27.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It's to facilitate other people becoming their own potential.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:27.94,1:40:30.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the reason to choose to continue on.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:30.94,1:40:33.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And that makes it all worth it.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:34.16,1:40:35.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, Lord, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:37.04,1:40:40.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, spiritual practice and daily life.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:40.84,1:40:42.52,Default,,0,0,0,,People say, how can I get more involved?
Dialogue: 0,1:40:44.31,1:40:45.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Goodwill towards all.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:45.51,1:40:46.59,Default,,0,0,0,,All of life, no matter what.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:47.15,1:40:50.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't forget, when the headsman comes to you, worry about how he's feeling.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:51.03,1:40:51.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't feel guilty.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:51.97,1:40:52.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It's okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:52.63,1:40:53.51,Default,,0,0,0,,You're doing your job.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:54.09,1:40:55.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm counting on you.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:55.31,1:40:55.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And tip him.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:58.55,1:40:59.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I always tip the headsman.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:04.13,1:41:05.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Goodwill towards all of life.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:05.65,1:41:05.81,Default,,0,0,0,,You see?
Dialogue: 0,1:41:07.00,1:41:07.32,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:07.44,1:41:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Spiritual practice and daily life.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:09.50,1:41:12.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to isolate yourself or discontinue.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:12.22,1:41:15.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And don't compartmentalize your life.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:15.36,1:41:17.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Become your own spiritual practice.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:17.22,1:41:21.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, when I give sermons someplace, I always say, you know, become the prayer.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:22.60,1:41:23.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Become that.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:23.62,1:41:24.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't practice that.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:24.92,1:41:25.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't think that.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:25.78,1:41:26.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't memorize that.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:26.84,1:41:27.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Be that.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:27.68,1:41:28.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Be that.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:28.26,1:41:28.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You know?
Dialogue: 0,1:41:28.60,1:41:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Be that.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:30.23,1:41:32.71,Default,,0,0,0,,So the practice is education.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:33.54,1:41:36.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And the choice of teachers.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:36.73,1:41:37.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Calibrate.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:37.27,1:41:40.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Always calibrate the teachers and calibrate the pathway.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:41.01,1:41:45.11,Default,,0,0,0,,In your daily routine, you include contemplation as a way of being in the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:45.11,1:41:47.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So when I say turn your life into a prayer,
Dialogue: 0,1:41:48.42,1:42:01.27,Default,,0,0,0,,you become that which is supportive of all of life and can see what the limitations of life are.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:01.27,1:42:07.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore, you tend to uplift life by virtue of that which you have become.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:08.55,1:42:13.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And meditation and contemplation become part of your life as does prayer.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:17.46,1:42:20.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Contemplation to me is a way of being in the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:20.46,1:42:24.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, meditation has its place.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:24.12,1:42:31.16,Default,,0,0,0,,But, and I spent many years meditating, but meditation tends to take you out of the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:32.06,1:42:35.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't function in today's world and spend all your time meditating.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:35.98,1:42:40.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I did it when I came out to wherever we are here.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:40.06,1:42:44.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And it didn't do anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:44.78,1:42:48.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I just stayed in that beatific state, you know, for, you know, just stayed there.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:49.06,1:42:50.84,Default,,0,0,0,,But you can't function in the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:50.84,1:42:56.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So being contemplative then is, I compare it to sort
Dialogue: 0,1:42:57.00,1:42:58.02,Default,,0,0,0,,of Yin position.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:58.02,1:43:04.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Contemplative means, you see, Yang is very this.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:04.10,1:43:07.20,Default,,0,0,0,,God, I got to have this, and I'm going to do that.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:07.20,1:43:11.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's very Yang.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:11.10,1:43:16.58,Default,,0,0,0,,A contemplative way of being in the world is a Yin posture.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:16.58,1:43:20.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Psychically you have become that which is open.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:20.78,1:43:27.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And by virtue of that which is open, your Yin side of you summons forth
Dialogue: 0,1:43:27.48,1:43:29.18,Default,,0,0,0,,that which you need.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:32.24,1:43:34.87,Default,,0,0,0,,You go to bed with a question on your mind
Dialogue: 0,1:43:34.87,1:43:37.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and you wake up and the answer is there.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:38.42,1:43:39.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Not through any doingness.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:42.24,1:43:44.22,Default,,0,0,0,,By virtue of that which you become,
Dialogue: 0,1:43:44.48,1:43:46.76,Default,,0,0,0,,your life becomes a supplication.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:47.88,1:43:51.78,Default,,0,0,0,,To thee, O Lord, do I surrender my will in the matter.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:51.78,1:43:54.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And you ask that the Lord reveal to you.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:55.34,1:43:58.70,Default,,0,0,0,,So you're asking so life becomes a continuous revelation
Dialogue: 0,1:43:58.70,1:44:04.19,Default,,0,0,0,,which eventually becomes the continuous miraculous.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:05.09,1:44:05.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:07.16,1:44:07.70,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:07.80,1:44:08.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So prayer then.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:10.24,1:44:10.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Dedication.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:11.74,1:44:13.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The other thing you begin to notice
Dialogue: 0,1:44:13.52,1:44:17.10,Default,,0,0,0,,is the incredible beauty and perfection of all that exists.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:17.76,1:44:20.36,Default,,0,0,0,,At first this sort of knocks you out
Dialogue: 0,1:44:20.36,1:44:21.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's very difficult to function.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:22.26,1:44:25.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Everywhere you go, the beauty is overwhelming.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:26.20,1:44:27.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I can remember being in an airport
Dialogue: 0,1:44:27.40,1:44:30.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and there's a couple of millions looked at each other
Dialogue: 0,1:44:30.79,1:44:31.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and I,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:31.33,1:44:33.13,Default,,0,0,0,,in the glance, you could see the love.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:33.63,1:44:35.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The presence of the love just knocked me out.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:35.53,1:44:36.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know how I got onto the plane.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:36.93,1:44:37.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I was just, it was just,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:39.27,1:44:42.37,Default,,0,0,0,,you're just blissed out by the incredible beauty
Dialogue: 0,1:44:42.37,1:44:43.47,Default,,0,0,0,,of all that exists.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:45.09,1:44:47.59,Default,,0,0,0,,As you walk through nature, you'll see the perfection.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:48.48,1:44:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,When you see the incredible beauty of weeds,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:50.88,1:44:52.18,Default,,0,0,0,,they stop being weeds.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:53.32,1:44:55.12,Default,,0,0,0,,When you walk by a weed and you look at it
Dialogue: 0,1:44:55.12,1:44:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and you see its incredible perfection,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:56.72,1:44:59.32,Default,,0,0,0,,there it stands there like the most magnificent sculpture.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:59.72,1:45:03.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You begin to see everything is like a magnificent sculpture.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:03.52,1:45:08.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Every weed stands there displaying its incredible perfection and beauty
Dialogue: 0,1:45:08.62,1:45:11.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and now you become conscious and you're witness
Dialogue: 0,1:45:11.02,1:45:13.72,Default,,0,0,0,,to the incredible perfection and beauty of all of creation.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:20.53,1:45:26.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Because creation is God manifest, the Godhead through creation.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:27.13,1:45:30.43,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see that creation is ongoing and forever.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:31.13,1:45:35.91,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no linear God with a beginning and an ending.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:35.91,1:45:37.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And the beginning was so-and-so.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:37.51,1:45:40.71,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a way of writing it up.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:42.06,1:45:44.16,Default,,0,0,0,,That which has no beginning has no ending.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:45.12,1:45:46.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, it has no cause.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:46.62,1:45:50.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So you live in a universe which is beyond causality.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:50.65,1:45:53.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And you see that everything is unfolding.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:53.35,1:45:58.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Its potentiality is actualizing by virtue of the infinite power of divinity,
Dialogue: 0,1:45:58.65,1:46:00.55,Default,,0,0,0,,which is the ultimate context.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:00.95,1:46:06.25,Default,,0,0,0,,The infinite power of divinity is an all-encompassing field of infinite power.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:07.25,1:46:13.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of which potentiality arises into actuality through emergence.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:13.08,1:46:14.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Through emergence.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:17.37,1:46:20.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, the potentiality of the human spirit,
Dialogue: 0,1:46:20.57,1:46:25.82,Default,,0,0,0,,the eventuality of it is inevitable.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:25.82,1:46:29.77,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to worry about spiritual evolution.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:29.77,1:46:30.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It's inevitable.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:31.77,1:46:33.77,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to work hard to avoid it.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:34.77,1:46:37.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the potentiality is within you and therefore,
Dialogue: 0,1:46:37.97,1:46:39.77,Default,,0,0,0,,in the infinite presence of divinity,
Dialogue: 0,1:46:39.97,1:46:42.17,Default,,0,0,0,,which is the source of all existence,
Dialogue: 0,1:46:42.17,1:46:44.37,Default,,0,0,0,,that which you can become,
Dialogue: 0,1:46:44.37,1:46:48.97,Default,,0,0,0,,that potentiality begins to manifest as an actuality.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:50.55,1:46:54.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, you watch the focus on the beauty of all things
Dialogue: 0,1:46:55.15,1:46:57.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and you note the perfection of all that exists.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:58.54,1:46:59.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You watch the unfoldment.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:59.94,1:47:01.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So there's no longer causality.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:01.84,1:47:03.24,Default,,0,0,0,,There's the unfoldment.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:03.64,1:47:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The willingness to surrender all these negativities.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:07.50,1:47:09.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The willingness to accept God's will.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:11.00,1:47:13.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The choices, situations, the ego and its problem.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:14.66,1:47:16.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, instead of being mad at the ego.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:16.26,1:47:18.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So now we have a new way of seeing the ego.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:19.06,1:47:25.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The ego is the leftover of the evolution of the protoplasm as the mammalian species.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:25.62,1:47:27.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It was necessary for survival.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:27.72,1:47:30.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It was what you owe your survival to.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:30.12,1:47:32.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Without the ego, you wouldn't be here to complain about your ego.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:34.72,1:47:38.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I say, thank you, ego, for getting me to the point that I can transcend, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:39.12,1:47:40.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Get off the bus,
Dialogue: 0,1:47:40.12,1:47:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and get on a different kind of a vehicle.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:42.42,1:47:44.02,Default,,0,0,0,,But without the bus, you wouldn't get there.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:44.02,1:47:50.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So God's willing to accept all these assets, the ego and its problems.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:50.50,1:47:53.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So instead of making the ego your enemy,
Dialogue: 0,1:47:54.10,1:47:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,you own it as though it's a pet.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:56.76,1:47:59.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It's your little pet, left over from prehistoric times.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:59.86,1:48:01.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, you hate other people.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:01.86,1:48:03.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, you want to be dominant.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:03.66,1:48:06.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, you want to be greedy and eat it all up.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:08.58,1:48:10.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, you want to copulate around the clock.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:10.58,1:48:11.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:11.98,1:48:15.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that your animal side?
Dialogue: 0,1:48:18.00,1:48:20.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You eventually accept God's infinite love and mercy.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:21.50,1:48:24.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And, all right, we'll go to the next one.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:24.10,1:48:25.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I forget which is the last chart.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:25.40,1:48:26.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Got to watch the time.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:27.16,1:48:28.16,Default,,0,0,0,,How much more time we got?
Dialogue: 0,1:48:30.75,1:48:31.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:31.25,1:48:31.65,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:31.65,1:48:31.95,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:33.06,1:48:33.46,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:33.66,1:48:37.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, these are practices to move you ahead in your level of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:38.26,1:48:43.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The more, the farther ahead you are in your level of consciousness, the more of what you hold in mind tends to materialize.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:43.16,1:48:48.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to be careful what you hold in mind because it's there, right there.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:48.46,1:48:51.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, choose holy company.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:51.88,1:48:57.70,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why, you know, avoid that which is obviously dedicated.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:57.70,1:48:57.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,1:48:57.90,1:48:59.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of their energy.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:59.20,1:49:00.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It's really just because of their energy.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:01.63,1:49:06.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, practice Socrates' view.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:06.89,1:49:09.69,Default,,0,0,0,,See others as being programmed.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:09.69,1:49:12.49,Default,,0,0,0,,They can't help being what they are because they've been programmed.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:13.19,1:49:14.49,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, the media program.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:14.89,1:49:16.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody all the time.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:16.59,1:49:18.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I hate to give you the statistics on it.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:18.49,1:49:21.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm working on a book called Spiritual Reality in Modern Man.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:21.59,1:49:22.69,Default,,0,0,0,,It's depressing.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:26.37,1:49:28.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I wish I'd never started that book.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:28.07,1:49:32.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I think when I knew less, I was happier.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:35.29,1:49:38.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, you calibrate the most, you know, popular shows on television.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:38.99,1:49:40.69,Default,,0,0,0,,You finally calibrate 160.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:41.19,1:49:41.99,Default,,0,0,0,,160.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:41.99,1:49:49.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Narcissism, cruelty, sexuality, seduction, 160.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:49.79,1:49:52.03,Default,,0,0,0,,See others as programmed.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:52.03,1:50:02.79,Default,,0,0,0,,You make a commitment, visualize your goal of loving this towards all of life and being grateful for what you have and be satisfied with where you're at.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:03.39,1:50:10.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, your mind tends to, the more often you choose a certain thing, the more likely you're going to choose that again.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:11.38,1:50:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,That's called quantum Zeno effect.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:14.00,1:50:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The quantum Zeno effect is out of randomness.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:18.00,1:50:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The more often you choose this, the more often you choose that.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:21.20,1:50:25.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Although the next time is potentially random, the more likely you will choose this, the more likely.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:26.20,1:50:27.70,Default,,0,0,0,,That's called the tension set.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:28.20,1:50:38.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So by declaration of spiritual intention and choosing constantly the good as you come to understand it, the likelihood is that you will choose it again.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:38.82,1:50:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So free will, of which there's all kinds of sophomoric argumentation, is a dominance of likelihoods, the attractor field that you have assigned to.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:50.32,1:50:50.92,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a greater.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:50.92,1:50:51.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Greater.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:51.32,1:50:53.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Likelihood that you will choose to forgive the person.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:53.72,1:50:57.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So even if you're angry and see them as wrong, you won't be satisfied with that.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:58.12,1:51:00.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You say, you know, he's a SOB.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:00.22,1:51:01.42,Default,,0,0,0,,He deserves what he gets.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:01.62,1:51:07.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Then in the bed, you think, but yeah, but the next day you so you meditate on it and you play with it.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:08.48,1:51:14.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And now you're not satisfied that you hate the guy or you fear the person, et cetera.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:14.18,1:51:15.08,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not satisfied.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:15.08,1:51:18.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Not because you have spiritual goals and you say, so you ask for a miracle.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:18.18,1:51:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You say, dear Lord, I'd like to see this differently.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:21.38,1:51:24.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And maybe nothing will happen at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:24.34,1:51:30.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Nelson, you're driving down the highway a month later and all of a sudden you got a totally different way of seeing it out of nowhere.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:31.34,1:51:33.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I can see now differently.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:33.74,1:51:34.84,Default,,0,0,0,,What else could he do?
Dialogue: 0,1:51:34.84,1:51:35.84,Default,,0,0,0,,What else could he do?
Dialogue: 0,1:51:36.64,1:51:38.64,Default,,0,0,0,,All he could do is hate you and kill you.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:38.64,1:51:40.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, what else could he do?
Dialogue: 0,1:51:40.24,1:51:42.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And then you forgive people for killing you.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:42.04,1:51:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Look how the times you've been killed.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:43.84,1:51:47.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't remember all those lifetimes, but even killed a lot, folks.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:47.64,1:51:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't kill.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:51.44,1:51:53.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Killed is one of the ways we usually ended it.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:53.54,1:51:55.65,Default,,0,0,0,,We got killed.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:55.65,1:52:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You end up with benevolence and mindfulness means paying attention to that mindset.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:02.88,1:52:06.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You're willing to surrender narcissism, the wonderful me.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:06.28,1:52:18.97,Default,,0,0,0,,You see how spiritual growth is not concordant with the current media world of you as the wonderful me.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:18.97,1:52:20.67,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, Time Magazine had one.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:20.67,1:52:22.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought Time Magazine cover was brilliant.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:22.97,1:52:27.89,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a stroke of genius, the mirror on the front of Time Magazine.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:28.39,1:52:32.79,Default,,0,0,0,,The ultimate, we are the ultimate of the narcissistic, me, self-indulgent.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:33.19,1:52:34.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's do it around the clock.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:38.46,1:52:40.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Me, wonderful me.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:40.66,1:52:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And my spot, my, you know, the blogs are now 90% of blogs are fallacious, you know, 90%.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:50.82,1:52:51.22,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:51.22,1:52:53.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So willing to surrender all the adrenaline.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:53.42,1:53:04.74,Default,,0,0,0,,The victimhood, the hurt feelings, look at the injustice collectors, willing to stop needing to win, and most importantly, to be right.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:04.74,1:53:09.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, to be right is one of the addictions that is very hard to get off.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:09.14,1:53:16.03,Default,,0,0,0,,To be right is so important, we're willing to die for it, and we're willing to kill you if you think you're right.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:16.03,1:53:21.10,Default,,0,0,0,,If you think you're right, you've just bought yourself a death sentence.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:21.10,1:53:23.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It's so important.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:24.63,1:53:26.13,Default,,0,0,0,,It's more important to be right.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:26.13,1:53:34.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And, of course, you watch the evening news channel, whatever they are, and you get over seeing yourself as the causal, primary causal agent.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:35.02,1:53:44.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You see yourself as only a part of a process in which your potentiality is actualizing because of the agreement of your own will.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:44.82,1:53:52.62,Default,,0,0,0,,If you decided against it with your will, then you've just shut off those options, but you've also shut off the karmic benefit of those options.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:54.41,1:53:55.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Forgiveness of self and others.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:55.91,1:54:02.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Selfless service, those are the great yogas, and, oh, I didn't tell you how to get off the mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:02.91,1:54:06.07,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll do that before we quit.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:06.07,1:54:13.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I know, we've got just time to kill the mind while we're here.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:13.14,1:54:25.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The mind is your biggest aggravation, and the classic spiritual writings are that enlightenment is between two thoughts.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:25.06,1:54:28.06,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a mistranslation of the Buddha, he never said such a thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:28.06,1:54:32.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, the people who listen to him, that's as far as they got it.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:32.28,1:54:35.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a ballpark.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:35.28,1:54:41.90,Default,,0,0,0,,No, the infinite is prior to thoughts.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:41.90,1:54:43.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It's below thoughts.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:43.90,1:54:45.90,Default,,0,0,0,,You cannot get between two thoughts.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:45.90,1:54:48.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Thoughts occur in one-tenth-thousandth of a second.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:48.60,1:54:54.60,Default,,0,0,0,,By the time you notice, by the time your perceiver perceives that, that one-tenth-thousandth is already gone.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:54.60,1:54:57.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The minute you begin to notice it, it's over already.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:57.10,1:54:59.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You cannot catch your own tail.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:59.60,1:55:01.60,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why enlightenment is very rare.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:01.60,1:55:02.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You practically never have it.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:02.60,1:55:03.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Never, never.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:03.60,1:55:06.52,Default,,0,0,0,,In a whole century, maybe, one or two.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:06.52,1:55:10.52,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're looking for enlightenment between two thoughts, you'll never find it.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:10.52,1:55:11.52,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:11.52,1:55:17.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The enlightenment is the nothingness, the potentiality, which is underneath your thoughts.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:17.52,1:55:20.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Your mind is actually still and silent.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:20.52,1:55:22.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Ninety-nine percent of your mind is still and silent.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:22.52,1:55:25.52,Default,,0,0,0,,One percent is busy thinking and talking.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:25.52,1:55:28.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And you pay attention to the one percent and think that's your mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:28.52,1:55:30.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll tell you right now where to find it.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:30.52,1:55:31.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Go away.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:31.52,1:55:33.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It's right now.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:33.55,1:55:37.55,Default,,0,0,0,,There is an infinite field of silence below your thoughts.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:37.55,1:55:38.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not prior.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:38.55,1:55:39.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not between.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:39.55,1:55:41.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It's underneath your thoughts.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:41.55,1:55:48.55,Default,,0,0,0,,All the thinkingness and mentalization is coming out of an infinite, silent field.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:48.55,1:55:52.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Then the thought of a little dogginess sort of grabs on.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:52.55,1:55:53.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Then it becomes Rover.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:53.55,1:55:59.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Then it becomes the story about a Rover got run over and oh, we all cried and married him and all.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:59.55,1:56:01.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Sad.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:01.99,1:56:11.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Underneath everybody's thinkingness right now, there's an infinite silence below all the thinkingness of everybody here.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:11.02,1:56:19.84,Default,,0,0,0,,There is nothing going on at all underneath the minds of everyone here.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:19.84,1:56:20.84,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a fact.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:20.84,1:56:21.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:21.84,1:56:22.84,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a fact.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:22.84,1:56:26.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Your mind is not thinking anything at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:26.58,1:56:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just an infinite, silent potentiality.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:30.48,1:56:33.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Your mind right now is not thinking anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:33.70,1:56:36.70,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a hearingness of this voice and its talkingness.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:36.70,1:56:40.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The only reason you can hear that is because your mind is actually silent.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:40.76,1:56:49.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Underneath the hearing of all this talkingness that's going on is an infinite, profound silence with no beginning and no end.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:49.99,1:56:52.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Forever.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:52.40,1:56:54.43,Default,,0,0,0,,An infinite potentiality.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:54.43,1:57:01.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody willing to give up thinking for two seconds?
Dialogue: 0,1:57:01.47,1:57:03.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's all quit thinking, okay?
Dialogue: 0,1:57:03.60,1:57:04.60,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:04.60,1:57:06.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, don't try to stop thinking.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:06.60,1:57:07.82,Default,,0,0,0,,If you try to stop thinking, you'll have to stop.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:07.82,1:57:12.52,Default,,0,0,0,,If you stop thinking, you'll be stuck with trying to stop thinking.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:12.52,1:57:14.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't stop thinking.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:14.52,1:57:15.52,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:15.52,1:57:24.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, we're going to dive below, like into the bottom of the sea.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:24.37,1:57:28.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Infinite silence.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:28.81,1:57:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,That's where it is, what you're looking for, is the infinite silence.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:35.00,1:57:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of the infinite silence, potentiality is actualizing into actuality, and that's what we call life.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:44.00,1:57:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what we call who I am.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:46.00,1:57:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what we call what the world is.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:48.00,1:57:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But you can see that's all just a presentation with no innate reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:54.00,1:57:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you're all free forever.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:57.00,1:57:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Lord.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:58.00,1:57:59.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:59.86,1:58:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,God bless you all.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:29.92,1:58:30.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It's been my joy.
